column7: SELECT DISTINCT T1.text FROM foreign_data AS T1 INNER JOIN cards AS T2 ON T2.uuid = T1.uuid INNER JOIN sets AS T3 ON T3.code = T2.setCode WHERE T3.name = 'Coldsnap' AND T1.language = 'Italian'

column5: Please list the Italian names of the cards in the set Coldsnap with the highest converted mana cost.
column6: card set Coldsnap refers to name = 'Coldsnap'; Italian refers to language = 'Italian'; highest converted mana cost refers to MAX(convertedManaCost)
column7: SELECT T2.name FROM foreign_data AS T1 INNER JOIN cards AS T2 ON T2.uuid = T1.uuid INNER JOIN sets AS T3 ON T3.code = T2.setCode WHERE T3.name = 'Coldsnap' AND T1.language = 'Italian' ORDER BY T2.convertedManaCost DESC

column5: When was the ruling for the card 'Reminisce' created?
column6: Reminisce refers to name = 'Reminisce'; when created is the date
column7: SELECT T2.date FROM cards AS T1 INNER JOIN rulings AS T2 ON T2.uuid = T1.uuid WHERE T1.name = 'Reminisce'

column5: What is the percentage of the cards with a converted mana cost of 7 in the set Coldsnap?
column6: converted mana cost of 7 refers to convertedManaCost = 7; card set Coldsnap refers to name = 'Coldsnap'; percentage = DIVIDE(SUM(convertedManaCost = 7), SUM(convertedManaCost))*100
column7: SELECT CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN T1.convertedManaCost = 7 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100 / COUNT(T1.id) FROM cards AS T1 INNER JOIN sets AS T2 ON T2.code = T1.setCode WHERE T2.name = 'Coldsnap'

column5: What is the percentage of incredibly powerful cards in the set Coldsnap?
column6: card set Coldsnap refers to name = 'Coldsnap'; foil is incredibly powerful refers to cardKingdomFoilId is not null AND cardKingdomId is not null; the percentage of incredibly powerful cards in the set refers to DIVIDE(SUM(incredibly powerful), SUM(name = 'Coldsnap'))*100
column7: SELECT CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN T1.cardKingdomFoilId IS NOT NULL AND T1.cardKingdomId IS NOT NULL THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100 / COUNT(T1.id) FROM cards AS T1 INNER JOIN sets AS T2 ON T2.code = T1.setCode WHERE T2.name = 'Coldsnap'

column5: For all cards illustrated by Jim Pavelec. and describe the text of the ruling of these cards. Do these cards have missing or degraded properties and values.
column6: all cards illustrated by Jim Pavelec refers to artist = 'Jim Pavelec'; the text of the ruling refers to text; cards have missing or degraded properties and values if hasContentWarning = 1 else it doesn't have;
column7: SELECT T2.text , CASE WHEN T1.hasContentWarning = 1 THEN 'YES' ELSE 'NO' END FROM cards AS T1 INNER JOIN rulings AS T2 ON T2.uuid = T1.uuid WHERE T1.artist = 'Jim Pavelec'

column5: What was the release date for the set which card "Evacuation" in it?
column6: Evacuation refers to name = 'Evacuation'; release date refers to releaseDate

column6: French refers to language = 'French'; "Tendo Ice Bridge" is a translated name of a card; translated name refers to translation

column5: What is the release date for the set "Ola de frÃ­o"?
column6: release date is the date of card set being released; set "Ola de frÃ­o" refers to translation = 'Ola de frÃ­o'

column5: When was the oldest mythic card released and what are its legal play formats?
column6: the oldest card refers to MIN(originalReleaseDate); mythic card refers to rarity = 'mythic'; legal play refers to status = 'legal'; play format refers to format
column7: SELECT T1.originalReleaseDate, T2.format FROM cards AS T1 INNER JOIN legalities AS T2 ON T1.uuid = T2.uuid WHERE T1.rarity = 'mythic' AND T1.originalReleaseDate IS NOT NULL AND T2.status = 'Legal' ORDER BY T1.originalReleaseDate LIMIT 1

column5: How many cards did Volkan BaÃ‡Âµa illustrated whose foreign language is in French?
column6: Volkan BaÃ‡Âµa refers to artist = 'Volkan BaÇµa'; foreign language is in French refers to language = 'French'
column7: SELECT COUNT(T3.id) FROM ( SELECT T1.id FROM cards AS T1 INNER JOIN foreign_data AS T2 ON T2.uuid = T1.uuid WHERE T1.artist = 'Volkan BaÇµa' AND T2.language = 'French' GROUP BY T1.id ) AS T3

column5: How many rare enchantment Abundance cards are there whose play format status are all legal?
column6: rare refers to rarity = 'rare'; enchantment card refers to types = 'Enchantment'; Abundance cards refers to name = 'Abundance'; format status are all legal refers to status = 'Legal'
column7: SELECT COUNT(T1.id) FROM cards AS T1 INNER JOIN legalities AS T2 ON T2.uuid = T1.uuid WHERE T1.rarity = 'rare' AND T1.types = 'Enchantment' AND T1.name = 'Abundance' AND T2.status = 'Legal'

column5: Which of the play format has the highest number of banned status? Indicate the play format and the names of all the card meet the condition.
column6: play format refers to format; banned status refers to status = 'Banned'; the highest number of banned status refers to MAX(COUNT(status = 'Banned'))
column7: WITH MaxBanned AS (SELECT format, COUNT(*) AS count_banned FROM legalities WHERE status = 'Banned' GROUP BY format ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC LIMIT 1) SELECT T2.format, T1.name FROM cards AS T1 INNER JOIN legalities AS T2 ON T2.uuid = T1.uuid INNER JOIN MaxBanned MB ON MB.format = T2.format WHERE T2.status = 'Banned'

column5: Who is the illustrator that illustrated the least amount of cards? List the format of play of the cards that he/she illustrated.
column6: format of the cards refers to format; illustrator refers to artist; the least amount of cards refers to MIN(artist)
column7: SELECT T1.artist, T2.format FROM cards AS T1 INNER JOIN legalities AS T2 ON T2.uuid = T1.uuid GROUP BY T1.artist ORDER BY COUNT(T1.id) ASC LIMIT 1

column5: Among the cards whose version of frame style is 1997, what is the status of the card illustrated by D. Alexander Gregory in legacy play format that has sensitive content or Wizards of the Coast?
column6: version of frame style is 1997 refers to frameVersion = '1997'; illustrated by D. Alexander Gregory refers to artist = 'D. Alexander Gregory'; sensitive content refers to hasContentWarning = 1; legacy play format refers to format = 'legacy'; status of the card refers to status
column7: SELECT DISTINCT T2.status FROM cards AS T1 INNER JOIN legalities AS T2 ON T2.uuid = T1.uuid WHERE T1.frameVersion = 1997 AND T1.hasContentWarning = 1 AND T1.artist = 'D. Alexander Gregory' AND T2.format = 'legacy'

column5: Which cards are ranked 1st on EDHRec? List all of the cards name and its banned play format.
column6: ranked 1st on EDHRec refers to edhrecRank = 1; banned refers to status = 'Banned'; play format refers to format; cards name refers to name
column7: SELECT T1.name, T2.format FROM cards AS T1 INNER JOIN legalities AS T2 ON T2.uuid = T1.uuid WHERE T1.edhrecRank = 1 AND T2.status = 'Banned' GROUP BY T1.name, T2.format

column5: What is the annual average number of sets that were released between 1/1/2012 to 12/31/2015? Indicate the common langugage of the card.
column6: AVG(id); releaseDate BETWEEN 1/1/2012 AND 12/31/2015; the common language refers to MAX(COUNT(language))
column7: SELECT (CAST(SUM(T1.id) AS REAL) / COUNT(T1.id)) / 4, T2.language FROM sets AS T1 INNER JOIN set_translations AS T2 ON T1.id = T2.id WHERE T1.releaseDate BETWEEN '2012-01-01' AND '2015-12-31' GROUP BY T1.releaseDate ORDER BY COUNT(T2.language) DESC LIMIT 1

column5: What are the rulings for the card named and designed by Kev Walker? List them in descending order of dates.
column6: rulings refers to text; card named and designed by Kev Walker refers to artist = 'Kev Walker'; descending order of dates refers to MAX(date);
column7: SELECT T2.text FROM cards AS T1 INNER JOIN rulings AS T2 ON T2.uuid = T1.uuid WHERE T1.artist = 'Kev Walker' ORDER BY T2.date DESC

column5: List the names of all the cards in the set Hour of Devastation and find the formats in which these cards are legal.
column6: the set Hour of Devastation refers to set.name = 'Hour of Devastation'; names of all the cards in the set refers to cards.name; legal cards refers to status = 'Legal'; the formats refers to format
column7: SELECT DISTINCT T2.name , CASE WHEN T1.status = 'Legal' THEN T1.format ELSE NULL END FROM legalities AS T1 INNER JOIN cards AS T2 ON T2.uuid = T1.uuid WHERE T2.setCode IN ( SELECT code FROM sets WHERE name = 'Hour of Devastation' )

column5: List all the frame styles and cards Allen Williams worked on and find any banned cards if there are any.
column6: frame styles refers to frameVersion; cards Allen Williams worked on refers to artist = 'Allen Williams'; banned cards refers to status = 'Banned'
column7: SELECT DISTINCT T1.frameVersion, T1.name , IIF(T2.status = 'Banned', T1.name, 'NO') FROM cards AS T1 INNER JOIN legalities AS T2 ON T1.uuid = T2.uuid WHERE T1.artist = 'Allen Williams'

column5: What is the average number of badges obtained by a user with over 200 views?
column6: user with over 200 views refers to Views > 200; average number of badges = Divide (Count(Id), Count(DisplayName))

column5: Among the posts with a score of over 5, what is the percentage of them being owned by an elder user?

column5: Give the only one comment text of the post with parent id 107829.

column5: User No.23853 gave a comment to a post at 9:08:18 on 2013/7/12, was that post well-finished?

column5: Among all the posts posted by the most influential user, identify the percentage with a score above 50.

column5: Paul di Resta was in the No. 853 race, what percent faster did he finish in the 853rd race than the next race for the fastest lap speed?
column6: Paul di Resta refers to the full name of the driver; Full name of the driver refers to drivers.forename ='Paul' and drivers.surname = 'di Resta'; race number refers to raceId; percentage = DIVIDE(SUBTRACT(fastestLapSpeed(raceId = 853), (fastestLapSpeed (raceId = 854)) * 100 , (fastestLapSpeed(raceId = 853))
column7: SELECT (SUM(IIF(T2.raceId = 853, T2.fastestLapSpeed, 0)) - SUM(IIF(T2.raceId = 854, T2.fastestLapSpeed, 0))) * 100 / SUM(IIF(T2.raceId = 853, T2.fastestLapSpeed, 0)) FROM drivers AS T1 INNER JOIN results AS T2 ON T2.driverId = T1.driverId WHERE T1.forename = 'Paul' AND T1.surname = 'di Resta'

column5: For the drivers who took part in the race in 1983/7/16, what's their race completion rate?

column7: SELECT CAST(COUNT(CASE WHEN T2.time IS NOT NULL THEN T2.driverId END) AS REAL) * 100 / COUNT(T2.driverId) FROM races AS T1 INNER JOIN results AS T2 ON T2.raceId = T1.raceId WHERE T1.date = '1983-07-16'

column5: In which country was the first European Grand Prix hosted? Name the circuit and location.

column5: What is the best lap time recorded? List the driver and race with such recorded lap time.

column5: What is the average lap time for Lewis Hamilton in the 2009 Malaysian Grand Prix?
column6: average lap time = AVG(milliseconds); 'Lewis Hamilton' refers to the full name of the driver; Full name of the driver refers to drivers.forename and drivers.surname; 'Malaysian Grand Prix' refers to races.name = 'Malaysian Grand Prix'
column7: SELECT AVG(T2.milliseconds) FROM races AS T1 INNER JOIN lapTimes AS T2 ON T2.raceId = T1.raceId INNER JOIN drivers AS T3 ON T3.driverId = T2.driverId WHERE T3.forename = 'Lewis' AND T3.surname = 'Hamilton' AND T1.year = 2009 AND T1.name = 'Malaysian Grand Prix'

column5: Calculate the percentage whereby Hamilton was not at the 1st track of the the f1 circuit since 2010.
column6: percentage = DIVIDE(COUNT(raceId) where surname = 'Hamilton' and position>1), (COUNT(raceId) where surname = 'Hamilton'); since 2010 refers to year >= 2010
column7: SELECT CAST(COUNT(CASE WHEN T2.position <> 1 THEN T2.position END) AS REAL) * 100 / COUNT(T2.driverStandingsId) FROM races AS T1 INNER JOIN driverStandings AS T2 ON T2.raceId = T1.raceId INNER JOIN drivers AS T3 ON T3.driverId = T2.driverId WHERE T3.surname = 'Hamilton' AND T1.year >= 2010

column5: Name the driver with the most winning. Mention his nationality and what is his maximum point scores.
column6: Full name of the driver refers to drivers.forename and drivers.surname; the most winning refers to MAX(COUNT(wins)); average point scores refers to MAX(points);
column7: SELECT T1.forename, T1.surname, T1.nationality, MAX(T2.points) FROM drivers AS T1 INNER JOIN driverStandings AS T2 ON T2.driverId = T1.driverId WHERE T2.wins >= 1 GROUP BY T1.forename, T1.surname, T1.nationality ORDER BY COUNT(T2.wins) DESC LIMIT 1

column5: What is the most laps f1 races had? Name the race, year and circuit location where the races with most laps was hosted.

column5: How many drivers from the UN participated in the 2008 Australian Grand Prix?

column5: Among the drivers that finished the race in the 2008 Chinese Grand Prix, how many of them have participated in Formula_1 races?
column6: COUNT(raceID) > 0 reveals that this driver participated in races; drivers who finished the race refers to time has value.
column7: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM ( SELECT T1.driverId FROM results AS T1 INNER JOIN races AS T2 on T1.raceId = T2.raceId WHERE T2.name = 'Chinese Grand Prix' AND T2.year = 2008 AND T1.time IS NOT NULL GROUP BY T1.driverId HAVING COUNT(T2.raceId) > 0 )

column5: How many points did Lewis Hamilton get in total in all the Formula_1 races he participated?

column5: What is the average fastest lap time in seconds for Lewis Hamilton in all the Formula_1 races?
column6: average fastest lap time = avg(fastestLapTime); The time is recorded on 'MM:SS.mmm'
column7: SELECT AVG(CAST(SUBSTR(T2.fastestLapTime, 1, INSTR(T2.fastestLapTime, ':') - 1) AS INTEGER) * 60 + CAST(SUBSTR(T2.fastestLapTime, INSTR(T2.fastestLapTime, ':') + 1) AS REAL)) FROM drivers AS T1 INNER JOIN results AS T2 ON T1.driverId = T2.driverId WHERE T1.surname = 'Hamilton' AND T1.forename = 'Lewis'

column5: What is the rate of drivers completing all the laps in the 2008 Australian Grand Prix?
column6: completing all the laps refers to time is not null; rate = divide(COUNT(raceID where time is not null), COUNT(raceID))
column7: SELECT CAST(SUM(IIF(T1.time IS NOT NULL, 1, 0)) AS REAL) * 100 / COUNT(T1.resultId) FROM results AS T1 INNER JOIN races AS T2 ON T1.raceId = T2.raceId WHERE T2.name = 'Australian Grand Prix' AND T2.year = 2008

column5: How much faster in percentage is the champion than the driver who finished the race last in the 2008 Australian Grand Prix?
column6: how much faster in percentage = divide(subtract(incremental time, champion time), last_driver time) * 100; last driver finished time = incremental time + champion time; only champion's finished time is represented by 'HH:MM:SS.mmm'; finished the game refers to time is not null
column7: WITH time_in_seconds AS ( SELECT T1.positionOrder, CASE WHEN T1.positionOrder = 1 THEN (CAST(SUBSTR(T1.time, 1, 1) AS REAL) * 3600) + (CAST(SUBSTR(T1.time, 3, 2) AS REAL) * 60) + CAST(SUBSTR(T1.time, 6) AS REAL) ELSE CAST(SUBSTR(T1.time, 2) AS REAL) END AS time_seconds FROM results AS T1 INNER JOIN races AS T2 ON T1.raceId = T2.raceId WHERE T2.name = 'Australian Grand Prix' AND T1.time IS NOT NULL AND T2.year = 2008 ), champion_time AS ( SELECT time_seconds FROM time_in_seconds WHERE positionOrder = 1), last_driver_incremental AS ( SELECT time_seconds FROM time_in_seconds WHERE positionOrder = (SELECT MAX(positionOrder) FROM time_in_seconds) ) SELECT (CAST((SELECT time_seconds FROM last_driver_incremental) AS REAL) * 100) / (SELECT time_seconds + (SELECT time_seconds FROM last_driver_incremental) FROM champion_time)

column5: What are the maximum points of British constructors?
column6: maximum points = MAX(points); British is a nationality
column7: SELECT MAX(T1.points) FROM constructorStandings AS T1 INNER JOIN constructors AS T2 on T1.constructorId = T2.constructorId WHERE T2.nationality = 'British'

column5: Which constructor has the highest point?
column7: SELECT T2.name FROM constructorStandings AS T1 INNER JOIN constructors AS T2 on T1.constructorId = T2.constructorId ORDER BY T1.points DESC LIMIT 1

column6: race at 291 refers to raceID = 291;

column5: How many Japanese constructors have 0 points in 2 races?

column7: SELECT COUNT(T1.raceId) FROM constructorStandings AS T1 INNER JOIN constructors AS T2 on T1.constructorId = T2.constructorId WHERE T1.points = 0 AND T2.nationality = 'Japanese' GROUP BY T1.constructorId HAVING COUNT(raceId) = 2

column5: Which constructors have been ranked 1?
column7: SELECT DISTINCT T2.name FROM results AS T1 INNER JOIN constructors AS T2 on T1.constructorId = T2.constructorId WHERE T1.rank = 1

column5: How many French constructors have a lap number of over 50?
column6: lap numbers of over 50 refers to laps > 50;

column5: Please calculate the race completion percentage of Japanese drivers from 2007 to 2009.
column6: from 2007 to 2009 refers to year between 2007 and 2009; race completion refers to time is not null; percentage = Divide(COUNT(DriverID where time is not null and year between 2007 and 2009),Count (DriverID where year between 2007 and 2009))*100;
column7: SELECT CAST(SUM(IIF(T1.time IS NOT NULL, 1, 0)) AS REAL) * 100 / COUNT(T1.raceId) FROM results AS T1 INNER JOIN races AS T2 on T1.raceId = T2.raceId INNER JOIN drivers AS T3 on T1.driverId = T3.driverId WHERE T3.nationality = 'Japanese' AND T2.year BETWEEN 2007 AND 2009

column5: What is the average time in seconds of champion for each year, before year 1975?
column6: only champion's finished time is represented by 'HH:MM:SS.mmm'; finished the game refers to time is not null; before year 1975 refers to year < 1975;
column7: WITH time_in_seconds AS ( SELECT T2.year, T2.raceId, T1.positionOrder, CASE WHEN T1.positionOrder = 1 THEN (CAST(SUBSTR(T1.time, 1, 1) AS REAL) * 3600) + (CAST(SUBSTR(T1.time, 3, 2) AS REAL) * 60) + CAST(SUBSTR(T1.time, 6,2) AS REAL )   + CAST(SUBSTR(T1.time, 9) AS REAL)/1000 ELSE 0 END AS time_seconds FROM results AS T1 INNER JOIN races AS T2 ON T1.raceId = T2.raceId WHERE T1.time IS NOT NULL ), champion_time AS ( SELECT year, raceId, time_seconds FROM time_in_seconds WHERE positionOrder = 1 ) SELECT year, AVG(time_seconds) FROM champion_time WHERE year < 1975 GROUP BY year HAVING AVG(time_seconds) IS NOT NULL

column5: Which drivers born after 1975 have been ranked 2? Please give their forenames and surnames.

column5: How many Italian drivers haven't finished the race?

column5: From 2000 to 2005, what percentage of drivers who were born before 1985 and the lap numbers were over 50?

column7: SELECT CAST(SUM(IIF(STRFTIME('%Y', T3.dob) < '1985' AND T1.laps > 50, 1, 0)) AS REAL) * 100 / COUNT(*) FROM results AS T1 INNER JOIN races AS T2 on T1.raceId = T2.raceId INNER JOIN drivers AS T3 on T1.driverId = T3.driverId WHERE T2.year BETWEEN 2000 AND 2005

column5: List down top 3 German drivers who has the shortest average pit stop duration and were born between 1980-1985.

column5: What is the average score of Lewis Hamilton among all the Turkish Grand Prix?

column5: In terms of the fastest lap time, what is the name of the race which recorded the fastest lap speed by a racer?

column5: Which racetrack hosted the most recent race? Indicate the full location.

column5: What is full name of the racer who ranked 1st in the 3rd qualifying race held in the Marina Bay Street Circuit in 2008?
column6: Ranked 1st in the 3rd qualifying race refer to MIN(q3); 2008 is the year of race; full name of racer = forename, surname
column7: SELECT T2.forename, T2.surname FROM qualifying AS T1 INNER JOIN drivers AS T2 on T1.driverId = T2.driverId INNER JOIN races AS T3 ON T1.raceid = T3.raceid WHERE q3 IS NOT NULL AND T3.year = 2008 AND T3.circuitId IN ( SELECT circuitId FROM circuits WHERE name = 'Marina Bay Street Circuit' ) ORDER BY CAST(SUBSTR(q3, 1, INSTR(q3, ':') - 1) AS INTEGER) * 60 + CAST(SUBSTR(q3, INSTR(q3, ':') + 1, INSTR(q3, '.') - INSTR(q3, ':') - 1) AS REAL) + CAST(SUBSTR(q3, INSTR(q3, '.') + 1) AS REAL) / 1000 ASC LIMIT 1

column5: As of the present, what is the full name of the youngest racer? Indicate her nationality and the name of the race to which he/she first joined.
column6: full name refers to forename+surname; Youngest racer = MAX(dob)
column7: SELECT T1.forename, T1.surname, T1.nationality, T3.name FROM drivers AS T1 INNER JOIN driverStandings AS T2 on T1.driverId = T2.driverId INNER JOIN races AS T3 on T2.raceId = T3.raceId ORDER BY JULIANDAY(T1.dob) DESC LIMIT 1

column5: How many accidents did the driver who had the highest number accidents in the Canadian Grand Prix have?
column6: number of accidents refers to the number where statusid = 3; Canadian Grand Prix refers to the race of name
column7: SELECT COUNT(T1.driverId) FROM results AS T1 INNER JOIN races AS T2 on T1.raceId = T2.raceId INNER JOIN status AS T3 on T1.statusId = T3.statusId WHERE T3.statusId = 3 AND T2.name = 'Canadian Grand Prix' GROUP BY T1.driverId ORDER BY COUNT(T1.driverId) DESC LIMIT 1

column5: How many wins was achieved by the oldest racer? Indicate his/her full name.

column5: During which lap did Lewis Hamilton take a pit stop during the 2011 Australian Grand Prix?

column5: Please list the time each driver spent at the pit stop during the 2011 Australian Grand Prix.
column6: time spent at pit stop refers to duration

column5: What is the lap record set by Lewis Hamilton in a Formula_1 race?
column6: lap recod means the fastest time recorded which refers to time
column7: SELECT T1.time FROM lapTimes AS T1 INNER JOIN drivers AS T2 on T1.driverId = T2.driverId WHERE T2.forename = 'Lewis' AND T2.surname = 'Hamilton'

column5: Which top 20 driver created the shortest lap time ever record in a Formula_1 race? Please give them full names.
column6: shortest lap time refers to MIN(time); the time format for the shortest lap time is 'MM:SS.mmm' or 'M:SS.mmm'; full name of the driver refers to forename, surname
column7: WITH lap_times_in_seconds AS (SELECT driverId, (CASE WHEN SUBSTR(time, 1, INSTR(time, ':') - 1) <> '' THEN CAST(SUBSTR(time, 1, INSTR(time, ':') - 1) AS REAL) * 60 ELSE 0 END + CASE WHEN SUBSTR(time, INSTR(time, ':') + 1, INSTR(time, '.') - INSTR(time, ':') - 1) <> '' THEN CAST(SUBSTR(time, INSTR(time, ':') + 1, INSTR(time, '.') - INSTR(time, ':') - 1) AS REAL) ELSE 0 END + CASE WHEN SUBSTR(time, INSTR(time, '.') + 1) <> '' THEN CAST(SUBSTR(time, INSTR(time, '.') + 1) AS REAL) / 1000 ELSE 0 END) AS time_in_seconds FROM lapTimes) SELECT T2.forename, T2.surname, T1.driverId FROM (SELECT driverId, MIN(time_in_seconds) AS min_time_in_seconds FROM lap_times_in_seconds GROUP BY driverId) AS T1 INNER JOIN drivers AS T2 ON T1.driverId = T2.driverId ORDER BY T1.min_time_in_seconds ASC LIMIT 20

column5: What was the position of the circuits during Lewis Hamilton's fastest lap in a Formula_1 race?
column6: fastest lap refers to MIN(time)
column7: SELECT T1.position FROM lapTimes AS T1 INNER JOIN drivers AS T2 on T1.driverId = T2.driverId WHERE T2.forename = 'Lewis' AND T2.surname = 'Hamilton' ORDER BY T1.time ASC LIMIT 1

column5: What is the lap record for the Austrian Grand Prix Circuit?
column6: lap record means the fastest time recorded which refers to time
column7: WITH fastest_lap_times AS ( SELECT T1.raceId, T1.fastestLapTime FROM results AS T1 WHERE T1.FastestLapTime IS NOT NULL) SELECT MIN(fastest_lap_times.fastestLapTime) as lap_record FROM fastest_lap_times INNER JOIN races AS T2 on fastest_lap_times.raceId = T2.raceId INNER JOIN circuits AS T3 on T2.circuitId = T3.circuitId WHERE T2.name = 'Austrian Grand Prix'

column5: Please list the lap records for the circuits in Italy.
column6: lap record means the fastest time recorded which refers to time
column7: WITH fastest_lap_times AS (SELECT T1.raceId, T1.FastestLapTime, (CAST(SUBSTR(T1.FastestLapTime, 1, INSTR(T1.FastestLapTime, ':') - 1) AS REAL) * 60) + (CAST(SUBSTR(T1.FastestLapTime, INSTR(T1.FastestLapTime, ':') + 1, INSTR(T1.FastestLapTime, '.') - INSTR(T1.FastestLapTime, ':') - 1) AS REAL)) + (CAST(SUBSTR(T1.FastestLapTime, INSTR(T1.FastestLapTime, '.') + 1) AS REAL) / 1000) as time_in_seconds FROM results AS T1 WHERE T1.FastestLapTime IS NOT NULL ) SELECT T1.FastestLapTime as lap_record FROM results AS T1 INNER JOIN races AS T2 on T1.raceId = T2.raceId INNER JOIN circuits AS T3 on T2.circuitId = T3.circuitId INNER JOIN (SELECT MIN(fastest_lap_times.time_in_seconds) as min_time_in_seconds FROM fastest_lap_times INNER JOIN races AS T2 on fastest_lap_times.raceId = T2.raceId INNER JOIN circuits AS T3 on T2.circuitId = T3.circuitId WHERE T3.country = 'Italy' ) AS T4 ON (CAST(SUBSTR(T1.FastestLapTime, 1, INSTR(T1.FastestLapTime, ':') - 1) AS REAL) * 60) + (CAST(SUBSTR(T1.FastestLapTime, INSTR(T1.FastestLapTime, ':') + 1, INSTR(T1.FastestLapTime, '.') - INSTR(T1.FastestLapTime, ':') - 1) AS REAL)) + (CAST(SUBSTR(T1.FastestLapTime, INSTR(T1.FastestLapTime, '.') + 1) AS REAL) / 1000) = T4.min_time_in_seconds LIMIT 1

column5: In which Formula_1 race was the lap record for the Austrian Grand Prix Circuit set?
column6: lap record means the fastest time recorded which refers to time
column7: WITH fastest_lap_times AS ( SELECT T1.raceId, T1.FastestLapTime, (CAST(SUBSTR(T1.FastestLapTime, 1, INSTR(T1.FastestLapTime, ':') - 1) AS REAL) * 60) + (CAST(SUBSTR(T1.FastestLapTime, INSTR(T1.FastestLapTime, ':') + 1, INSTR(T1.FastestLapTime, '.') - INSTR(T1.FastestLapTime, ':') - 1) AS REAL)) + (CAST(SUBSTR(T1.FastestLapTime, INSTR(T1.FastestLapTime, '.') + 1) AS REAL) / 1000) as time_in_seconds FROM results AS T1 WHERE T1.FastestLapTime IS NOT NULL ) SELECT T2.name FROM races AS T2 INNER JOIN circuits AS T3 on T2.circuitId = T3.circuitId INNER JOIN results AS T1 on T2.raceId = T1.raceId INNER JOIN ( SELECT MIN(fastest_lap_times.time_in_seconds) as min_time_in_seconds FROM fastest_lap_times INNER JOIN races AS T2 on fastest_lap_times.raceId = T2.raceId INNER JOIN circuits AS T3 on T2.circuitId = T3.circuitId WHERE T2.name = 'Austrian Grand Prix') AS T4 ON (CAST(SUBSTR(T1.FastestLapTime, 1, INSTR(T1.FastestLapTime, ':') - 1) AS REAL) * 60) + (CAST(SUBSTR(T1.FastestLapTime, INSTR(T1.FastestLapTime, ':') + 1, INSTR(T1.FastestLapTime, '.') - INSTR(T1.FastestLapTime, ':') - 1) AS REAL)) + (CAST(SUBSTR(T1.FastestLapTime, INSTR(T1.FastestLapTime, '.') + 1) AS REAL) / 1000) = T4.min_time_in_seconds WHERE T2.name = 'Austrian Grand Prix'

column5: In the race a driver set the lap record for the Austrian Grand Prix Circuit, how long did he spent at the pit stop at that same race?
column6: lap record means the fastest time recorded which refers to time, how long spent at pitstop refers to duration
column7: WITH fastest_lap_times AS ( SELECT T1.raceId, T1.driverId, T1.FastestLapTime, (CAST(SUBSTR(T1.FastestLapTime, 1, INSTR(T1.FastestLapTime, ':') - 1) AS REAL) * 60) + (CAST(SUBSTR(T1.FastestLapTime, INSTR(T1.FastestLapTime, ':') + 1, INSTR(T1.FastestLapTime, '.') - INSTR(T1.FastestLapTime, ':') - 1) AS REAL)) + (CAST(SUBSTR(T1.FastestLapTime, INSTR(T1.FastestLapTime, '.') + 1) AS REAL) / 1000) as time_in_seconds FROM results AS T1 WHERE T1.FastestLapTime IS NOT NULL), lap_record_race AS ( SELECT T1.raceId, T1.driverId FROM results AS T1 INNER JOIN races AS T2 on T1.raceId = T2.raceId INNER JOIN circuits AS T3 on T2.circuitId = T3.circuitId INNER JOIN ( SELECT MIN(fastest_lap_times.time_in_seconds) as min_time_in_seconds FROM fastest_lap_times INNER JOIN races AS T2 on fastest_lap_times.raceId = T2.raceId INNER JOIN circuits AS T3 on T2.circuitId = T3.circuitId WHERE T2.name = 'Austrian Grand Prix') AS T4 ON (CAST(SUBSTR(T1.FastestLapTime, 1, INSTR(T1.FastestLapTime, ':') - 1) AS REAL) * 60) + (CAST(SUBSTR(T1.FastestLapTime, INSTR(T1.FastestLapTime, ':') + 1, INSTR(T1.FastestLapTime, '.') - INSTR(T1.FastestLapTime, ':') - 1) AS REAL)) + (CAST(SUBSTR(T1.FastestLapTime, INSTR(T1.FastestLapTime, '.') + 1) AS REAL) / 1000) = T4.min_time_in_seconds WHERE T2.name = 'Austrian Grand Prix') SELECT T4.duration FROM lap_record_race INNER JOIN pitStops AS T4 on lap_record_race.raceId = T4.raceId AND lap_record_race.driverId = T4.driverId

column5: Please list the location coordinates of the circuits whose lap record is 1:29.488.
column6: lap records means the fastest time recorded which refers to time; coordinates are expressed as latitude and longitude which refers to (lat, lng)
column7: SELECT T3.lat, T3.lng FROM lapTimes AS T1 INNER JOIN races AS T2 on T1.raceId = T2.raceId INNER JOIN circuits AS T3 on T2.circuitId = T3.circuitId WHERE T1.time = '1:29.488'

column5: What was the average time in milliseconds Lewis Hamilton spent at a pit stop during Formula_1 races?
column6: average time in milliseconds spent at pit stop refers to AVG(milliseconds)
column7: SELECT AVG(milliseconds) FROM pitStops AS T1 INNER JOIN drivers AS T2 on T1.driverId = T2.driverId WHERE T2.forename = 'Lewis' AND T2.surname = 'Hamilton'

column5: What is the average lap time in milliseconds of all the lap records set on the various circuits in Italy?
column6: average = AVG(milliseconds)
column7: SELECT CAST(SUM(T1.milliseconds) AS REAL) / COUNT(T1.lap) FROM lapTimes AS T1 INNER JOIN races AS T2 on T1.raceId = T2.raceId INNER JOIN circuits AS T3 on T2.circuitId = T3.circuitId WHERE T3.country = 'Italy'

column5: At present, calculate for the player's age who have a sprint speed of no less than 97 between 2013 to 2015.
column6: players age at present = SUBTRACT((DATETIME(), birthday)); sprint speed of no less than 97 refers to sprint_speed > = 97; between 2013 to 2015 refers to YEAR(date) > = '2013' AND YEAR(date) < = '2015';
column7: SELECT DISTINCT DATETIME() - T2.birthday age FROM Player_Attributes AS t1 INNER JOIN Player AS t2 ON t1.player_api_id = t2.player_api_id WHERE STRFTIME('%Y',t1.`date`) >= '2013' AND STRFTIME('%Y',t1.`date`) <= '2015' AND t1.sprint_speed >= 97

column5: Who has the highest average finishing rate between the highest and shortest football player?
column6: finishing rate refers to finishing; highest average finishing rate = MAX(AVG(finishing)); highest football player refers to MAX(height); shortest football player refers to MIN(height);
column7: SELECT A FROM ( SELECT AVG(finishing) result, 'Max' A FROM Player AS T1 INNER JOIN Player_Attributes AS T2 ON T1.player_api_id = T2.player_api_id WHERE T1.height = ( SELECT MAX(height) FROM Player ) UNION SELECT AVG(finishing) result, 'Min' A FROM Player AS T1 INNER JOIN Player_Attributes AS T2 ON T1.player_api_id = T2.player_api_id WHERE T1.height = ( SELECT MIN(height) FROM Player ) ) ORDER BY result DESC LIMIT 1

column5: What is the average number of goals made by Parma as the away team while playing in Italy?
column6: Parma refers to team_long_name = 'Parma'; average number of goals refers to AVG(away_team_goal)
column7: SELECT CAST(SUM(T1.away_team_goal) AS REAL) / COUNT(T1.id) FROM "Match" AS T1 INNER JOIN TEAM AS T2 ON T1.away_team_api_id = T2.team_api_id INNER JOIN Country AS T3 ON T1.country_id = T3.id WHERE T2.team_long_name = 'Parma' AND T3.name = 'Italy'

column5: What is the average heights of Italy players?
column6: average heights refers to Avg(height); Italy is name of country
column7: SELECT CAST(SUM(T1.height) AS REAL) / COUNT(T1.id) FROM Player AS T1 INNER JOIN Match AS T2 ON T1.id = T2.id INNER JOIN Country AS T3 ON T2.country_id = T3.ID WHERE T3.NAME = 'Italy'

column5: What is the disease patient '30609' diagnosed with. List all the date of laboratory tests done for this patient.
column6: 30609' is the Patient ID; disease means Diagnosis
column7: SELECT T1.Diagnosis, T2.Date FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T1.ID = 30609

column5: State the sex and birthday of patient ID '163109'. When was the examination taken and what symptom does the patient had.
column6: When was the examination taken refers to `Examination Date`
column7: SELECT T1.SEX, T1.Birthday, T2.`Examination Date`, T2.Symptoms FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Examination AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T1.ID = 163109

column5: List the patient ID, sex and birthday of patient with LDH beyond normal range.
column6: LDH beyond normal range refers to LDH > '500';
column7: SELECT DISTINCT T1.ID, T1.SEX, T1.Birthday FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.LDH > 500

column5: State the ID and age of patient with positive degree of coagulation.
column6: age refers to SUBTRACT(year(current_timestamp), year(Birthday)); positive degree of coagulation refers to RVVT = '+';
column7: SELECT DISTINCT T1.ID, STRFTIME('%Y', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP) - STRFTIME('%Y', T1.Birthday) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Examination AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.RVVT = '+'

column5: For patients with severe degree of thrombosis, list their ID, sex and disease the patient is diagnosed with.
column6: severe degree of thrombosis refers to thrombosis = 2; disease refers to diagnosis;
column7: SELECT DISTINCT T1.ID, T1.SEX, T1.Diagnosis FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Examination AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.Thrombosis = 2

column5: List all patients who were born in 1937 whose total cholesterol was beyond the normal range.
column6: who were born in 1937 refers to year(birthday) = '1937'; total cholesterol was beyond the normal range refers to `T-CHO` > = '250'
column7: SELECT DISTINCT T1.ID FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE STRFTIME('%Y', T1.Birthday) = '1937' AND T2.`T-CHO` >= 250

column5: For patient with albumin level lower than 3.5, list their ID, sex and diagnosis.
column6: albumin level lower than 3.5 refers to ALB < 3.5;
column7: SELECT DISTINCT T1.ID, T1.SEX, T1.Diagnosis FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.ALB < 3.5

column5: What is the percentage of female patient had total protein not within the normal range?
column6: female refers to sex = 'F'; total protein not within the normal range refers to TP < '6.0' or TP > '8.5'; calculation = DIVIDE((ID where sex = 'F' and TP < '6.0' or TP > '8.5'), COUNT(ID)) * 100
column7: SELECT CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN T1.SEX = 'F' AND (T2.TP < 6.0 OR T2.TP > 8.5) THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100 / COUNT(*) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T1.SEX = 'F'

column5: For in-patient age 50 and above, what is their average anti-cardiolipin antibody (IgG) concentration?
column6: in-patient refers to Admission = '+'; age 50 and above refers to SUBTRACT(year(current_timestamp), year(Birthday)) >= '50'; average anti-cardiolipin antibody (IgG) concentration refers to AVG(aCL IgG)
column7: SELECT AVG(T2.`aCL IgG`) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Examination AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE STRFTIME('%Y', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP) - STRFTIME('%Y', T1.Birthday) >= 50 AND T1.Admission = '+'

column5: How many of the patients with the most serious thrombosis cases examined in 1997 are women?
column6: the most serious thrombosis refers to Thrombosis = '1' (the most severe one); women refers to sex = 'F'
column7: SELECT  COUNT(*) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Examination AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T1.SEX = 'F' AND STRFTIME('%Y', T2.`Examination Date`) = '1997' AND T2.Thrombosis = 1

column5: What is the age gap between the youngest and oldest patient with a normal triglyceride recorded?
column6: age gap refers to SUBTRACT(MAX(year(Birthday)) - MIN(year(Birthday))); normal triglyceride refers to tg > = 200
column7: SELECT STRFTIME('%Y', MAX(T1.Birthday)) - STRFTIME('%Y', MIN(T1.Birthday)) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.TG >= 200

column5: What are the symptoms observed by the youngest patient to ever did a medical examination? Identify their diagnosis.
column6: The larger the birthday value, the younger the person is, and vice versa; symptoms observed refers to the symptoms is not NULL
column7: SELECT T2.Symptoms, T1.Diagnosis FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Examination AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.Symptoms IS NOT NULL ORDER BY T1.Birthday DESC LIMIT 1

column5: For the year that concluded on December 31, 1998, how many male patients on average were tested in the lab each month?
column6: the year that concluded on December 31, 1998 refers to Date BETWEEN '1998-01-01' AND '1998-12-31'; male refers to SEX = 'M'; calculation = DIVIDE(COUNT(ID), 12)
column7: SELECT CAST(COUNT(T1.ID) AS REAL) / 12 FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE STRFTIME('%Y', T2.Date) = '1998' AND T1.SEX = 'M'

column5: The oldest SJS patient's medical laboratory work was completed on what date, and what age was the patient when they initially arrived at the hospital?
column6: The larger the birthday value, the younger the person is, and vice versa; 'SJS' refers to diagnosis; (SUBTRACT(year(`First Date`)), year(Birthday)); age of the patients when they initially arrived at the hospital refers to year(Birthday)
column7: SELECT T1.Date, STRFTIME('%Y', T2.`First Date`) - STRFTIME('%Y', T2.Birthday),T2.Birthday FROM Laboratory AS T1 INNER JOIN Patient AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.Diagnosis = 'SJS' AND T2.Birthday IS NOT NULL ORDER BY T2.Birthday ASC LIMIT 1

column5: What is the ratio of male to female patients among all those with abnormal uric acid counts?
column6: male refers to SEX = 'M'; female refers to SEX = 'F'; abnormal uric acid refers to UA < = '8.0' where SEX = 'M', UA < = '6.5' where SEX = 'F'; calculation = DIVIDE(SUM(UA <= '8.0' and SEX = 'M'), SUM(UA <= '6.5 and SEX = 'F'))
column7: SELECT CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN T2.UA <= 8.0 AND T1.SEX = 'M' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) / SUM(CASE WHEN T2.UA <= 6.5 AND T1.SEX = 'F' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID

column5: How many patients hadn't undergone a medical examination until at least a year following their initial hospital visit?
column6: hadn't undergone a medical examination until at least a year refers to SUBTRACT(year(`Examination Date`), year(`First Date`)) > = 1
column7: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Examination AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T1.Admission = '+' AND STRFTIME('%Y', T2.`Examination Date`) - STRFTIME('%Y', T1.`First Date`) >= 1

column5: How many underage patients were examined during the course of the three-year period from 1990 to 1993?
column6: underage patients refers to year(Birthday) < 18; three-year period from 1990 to 1993 refers to year(`Examination Date`) between '1990' and '1993'
column7: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Examination AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE STRFTIME('%Y', T2.`Examination Date`) BETWEEN '1990' AND '1993' AND STRFTIME('%Y', T2.`Examination Date`) - STRFTIME('%Y', T1.Birthday) < 18

column5: How many male patients have elevated total bilirubin count?
column6: male refers to SEX = 'M'; elevated means above the normal range; total bilirubin above the normal range refers to `T-BIL` >= '2.0'
column7: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.`T-BIL` >= 2.0 AND T1.SEX = 'M'

column5: What is the most common illness that doctors identified among the patients whose lab work was done between 1/1/1985, and 12/31/1995?
column6: the most common illness refers to MAX(COUNT(Diagnosis)); lab work between 1/1/1985 and 12/31/1995 refers to `Examination Date` between '1985-01-01' and '1995-12-31 '
column7: SELECT T2.Diagnosis FROM Examination AS T1 INNER JOIN Patient AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T1.`Examination Date` BETWEEN '1985-01-01' AND '1995-12-31' GROUP BY T2.Diagnosis ORDER BY COUNT(T2.Diagnosis) DESC LIMIT 1

column5: What is the average age of patients as of year 1999 examined in the laboratory for the October of the year 1991?
column6: average age of patients as of year 1999 refers to AVG(SUBTRACT('1999', year(Birthday))); October of 1991 refers to Date BETWEEN '1991-10-01' AND '1991-10-30'
column7: SELECT AVG('1999'  - STRFTIME('%Y', T2.Birthday)) FROM Laboratory AS T1 INNER JOIN Patient AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T1.Date BETWEEN '1991-10-01' AND '1991-10-30'

column5: How old was the patient who had the highest hemoglobin count at the time of the examination, and what is the doctor's diagnosis?
column6: How old the patient refers to SUBTRACT(year(`Examination Date`), year(Birthday)); the highest hemoglobin count refers to MAX(HGB)
column7: SELECT STRFTIME('%Y', T2.Date) - STRFTIME('%Y', T1.Birthday), T1.Diagnosis FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID ORDER BY T2.HGB DESC LIMIT 1

column5: Was the patient a man or a women whose ALT glutamic pylvic transaminase status got 9 on 1992-6-12?
column6: man refers to SEX = 'M'; women refers to SEX = 'F'; ALT glutamic pylvic transaminase status got 9 GPT = '9'; 1992/6/12 refers to Date = '1992-06-12'
column7: SELECT T1.SEX FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.GPT = 9.0 AND T2.Date = '1992-06-12'

column5: For the patient who got the laboratory test of uric acid level as 8.4 on 1991-10-21, how old was he/she at that time?
column6: how old at that time refers to SUBTRACT(year(test date), year(Birthday)); uric acid level as 8.4 refers to UA = '8.4'; 1991/10/21 refers to Date = '1991-10-21'
column7: SELECT STRFTIME('%Y', T2.Date) - STRFTIME('%Y', T1.Birthday) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.UA = 8.4 AND T2.Date = '1991-10-21'

column5: For the patient who was diagnosed SLE on 1997/1/27, what was his/her original diagnose when he/she came to the hospital for the first time?
column6: SLE' AND original diagnose refers to diagnosis; 1997/1/27 refer to `Examination Date` = '1997-01-27'; first came to the hospital refers to patient.`First Date`
column7: SELECT T1.Diagnosis FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Examination AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T1.ID = ( SELECT ID FROM Examination WHERE `Examination Date` = '1997-01-27' AND Diagnosis = 'SLE' ) AND T2.`Examination Date` = T1.`First Date`

column5: For the patient whose birthday was 1959/3/1, what symptoms did he/she have during the examination on 1993/9/27?
column7: SELECT T2.Symptoms FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Examination AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T1.Birthday = '1959-03-01' AND T2.`Examination Date` = '1993-09-27'

column5: For the patient who was born on 1959/2/18, what is the decrease rate for his/her total cholesterol from November to December in 1981?
column6: born on 1959/2/18 refers to Birthday = '1959-02-18'; calculation = SUBTRACT(SUM(Birthday = '1959-02-18' and Date like '1981-11-%' THEN `T-CHO`), SUM(Birthday = '1959-02-18' and Date like '1981-12-%' THEN `T-CHO`))
column7: SELECT CAST((SUM(CASE WHEN T2.Date LIKE '1981-11-%' THEN T2.`T-CHO` ELSE 0 END) - SUM(CASE WHEN T2.Date LIKE '1981-12-%' THEN T2.`T-CHO` ELSE 0 END)) AS REAL) / SUM(CASE WHEN T2.Date LIKE '1981-12-%' THEN T2.`T-CHO` ELSE 0 END) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T1.Birthday = '1959-02-18'

column5: List all patients who were followed up at the outpatient clinic who underwent a laboratory test in October 1991 and had a total blood bilirubin level within the normal range.
column6: followed up at the outpatient clinic refers to Admission = '-'; laboratory test in April 1981 refers to Date like '1991-10%'; blood bilirubin level within the normal range refers to T-BIL < 2.0;
column7: SELECT DISTINCT T1.ID FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T1.Admission = '-' AND T2.`T-BIL` < 2.0 AND T2.Date LIKE '1991-10-%'

column5: Excluding all P only ANA Pattern patients, how many of the remainder are women born between 1980 and 1989?
column6: Excluding all P only ANA Pattern refers to `ANA Pattern`! = 'P'; women refers to SEX = 'F'; born between 1980 and 1989 refers to BIRTHDAY
column7: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Examination AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.`ANA Pattern` != 'P' AND STRFTIME('%Y', T1.Birthday) BETWEEN '1980' AND '1989' AND T1.SEX = 'F'

column5: What sex is the patient who in a medical examination was diagnosed with PSS and in a laboratory examination had a blood level of C-reactive protein de 2+, createnine 1 and LDH 123?
column6: PSS' refers to diagnosis; blood level of C-reactive protein de 2+refers to CRP > 2; createnine 1 refers to CRE = 1; LDH 123 refers to LDH = 123
column7: SELECT T1.SEX FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Examination AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T3 ON T3.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.Diagnosis = 'PSS' AND T3.CRP = '2+' AND T3.CRE = 1.0 AND T3.LDH = 123

column5: What is the average blood albumin level for female patients with a PLT greater than 400 who have been diagnosed with SLE?
column6: average blood albumin level refers to AVG(ALB); female refers to SEX = 'F'; PLT greater than 400 refers to PLT > 400; diagnosed with SLE refers to Diagnosis= 'SLE'
column7: SELECT AVG(T2.ALB) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.PLT > 400 AND T1.Diagnosis = 'SLE' AND T1.SEX = 'F'

column5: How many male patients who underwent testing between 1995 and 1997 and were subsequently diagnosed with Behcet disease did not stay in the hospital for treatment?
column6: male refers to SEX = 'M'; underwent testing between 1995 and 1997 refers to `Examination Date` between '1995' and '1997'; Behcet refers to diagnosis; did not stay in the hospital refers to Admission = '-'
column7: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Examination AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.Diagnosis = 'Behcet' AND T1.SEX = 'M' AND STRFTIME('%Y', T2.`Examination Date`) BETWEEN '1995' AND '1997' AND T1.Admission = '-'

column5: How many patients who were female got white blood cells that were below 3.5?
column6: female refers to SEX = 'F'; white blood cells that were below 3.5 refers to WBC < 3.5
column7: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.WBC < 3.5 AND T1.SEX = 'F'

column5: How long did it take after patient number 821298 arrived at the hospital for the first time before her evaluation began?
column6: DATEDIFF(`Examination Date`, `First Date`)
column7: SELECT STRFTIME('%d', T3.`Examination Date`) - STRFTIME('%d', T1.`First Date`) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Examination AS T3 ON T1.ID = T3.ID WHERE T1.ID = 821298

column5: Was the patient with the number 57266's uric acid within a normal range?
column6: uric acid within a normal range refers to UA > 8.0 and SEX = 'M'OR UA > 6.5 and SEX = 'F'
column7: SELECT CASE WHEN (T1.SEX = 'F' AND T2.UA > 6.5) OR (T1.SEX = 'M' AND T2.UA > 8.0) THEN true ELSE false END FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T1.ID = 57266

column5: List all patients with their sex and date of birthday, whose AST glutamic oxaloacetic transaminase (GOT) index is within normal range for loboratory examination in 1994.
column6: AST glutamic oxaloacetic transaminase (GOT) index is within normal range refers to GOT < 60; examination in 1994 refers to year(Date) = 1994
column7: SELECT DISTINCT T1.SEX, T1.Birthday FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.GOT < 60 AND STRFTIME('%Y', T2.Date) = '1994'

column5: Provide IDs for male patients with ALT glutamic pylvic transaminase (GPT) that have history of ALT glutamic pylvic transaminase (GPT) exceed the normal range.
column6: male refers to SEX = 'M'; ALT glutamic pylvic transaminase (GPT) exceed the normal range refers to GPT > = 60
column7: SELECT DISTINCT T1.ID FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T1.SEX = 'M' AND T2.GPT >= 60

column5: Please provide the diagnosis of patients with ALT glutamic pylvic transaminase beyond the normal range by ascending order of their date of birth.
column6: ALT glutamic pylvic transaminase beyond the normal range refers to GPT > 60; The larger the birthday value, the younger the person is, and vice versa;
column7: SELECT DISTINCT T1.Diagnosis FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.GPT > 60 ORDER BY T1.Birthday ASC

column5: Provide the ID and age of patient with lactate dehydrogenase (LDH) between 100-300 index above the normal range.
column6: age refers to SUBTRACT(year(current_timestamp), year(Birthday)); lactate dehydrogenase (LDH) between 100-300 index above the normal range refers to LDH between 600 and 800;
column7: SELECT DISTINCT T1.ID, STRFTIME('%Y', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP) - STRFTIME('%Y', T1.Birthday) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.LDH > 600 AND T2.LDH < 800

column5: For patients with alkaliphophatase (ALP) within normal range, were they treated as inpatient or outpatient?
column6: alkaliphophatase (ALP) within normal range refers to ALP < 300; inpatient refers to admission = '+'; outpatient refers to admission = '-'
column7: SELECT T1.Admission FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.ALP < 300

column5: Name the ID of the patient who is born on the April 1st, 1982. Is his/her alkaliphophatase (ALP) within normal range?
column6: alkaliphophatase (ALP) within normal range refers to ALP < 300
column7: SELECT T1.ID , CASE WHEN T2.ALP < 300 THEN 'normal' ELSE 'abNormal' END FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T1.Birthday = '1982-04-01'

column5: List ID, sex and date of birth of patient whose total protein (TP) below the lower range of the normal index.
column6: total protein (TP) below the lower range of the normal index refers to TP < 6.0
column7: SELECT DISTINCT T1.ID, T1.SEX, T1.Birthday FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.TP < 6.0

column5: For all female patient with total protein (TP) beyond the normal index, what is the deviation of their TP idex from the normal.
column6: female refers to SEX = 'F'; total protein (TP) beyond the normal index refers to TP > 8.5; deviation of TP index from normal refers to SUBTRACT(TP, 8.5)
column7: SELECT T2.TP - 8.5 FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T1.SEX = 'F' AND T2.TP > 8.5

column5: Sort in descending order all patients by birthday for male patient with albumin not within range.
column6: male = SEX = 'M'; albumin not within range refers to ALB < = 3.5 or ALB > = 5.5
column7: SELECT DISTINCT T1.ID FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T1.SEX = 'M' AND (T2.ALB <= 3.5 OR T2.ALB >= 5.5) ORDER BY T1.Birthday DESC

column5: For all patient born in 1982, state if their albumin is within normal range.
column6: Year(Birthday) = '1982'; albumin is within normal range refers to ALB between 3.5 and 5.5
column7: SELECT CASE WHEN T2.ALB >= 3.5 AND T2.ALB <= 5.5 THEN 'normal' ELSE 'abnormal' END FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE STRFTIME('%Y', T1.Birthday) = '1982'

column5: What is the percentage of the female patient whose uric acid (UA) beyond the normal range?
column6: uric acid (UA) beyond the normal range refers to UA > 8.0 and SEX = 'M' or UA > 6.5 and SEX = 'F'; female refers to Sex = 'F'
column7: SELECT CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN T2.UA > 6.5 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100 / COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T1.SEX = 'F'

column5: For all patients with normal uric acid (UA), what is the average UA index based on their latest laboratory examination result?
column6: uric acid (UA) with normal range refers to UA < 8.0 and SEX = 'M' or UA < 6.5 and SEX = 'F'; average UA index refers to AVG(UA)
column7: SELECT AVG(T2.UA) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE (T2.UA < 6.5 AND T1.SEX = 'F') OR (T2.UA < 8.0 AND T1.SEX = 'M') AND T2.Date = ( SELECT MAX(Date) FROM Laboratory )

column5: Provide all ID, sex and birthday of patients whose urea nitrogen (UN) just within the borderline of passing?
column6: urea nitrogen (UN) just within the borderline of passing refers to UN = 29;
column7: SELECT DISTINCT T1.ID, T1.SEX, T1.Birthday FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.UN = 29

column5: Provide the ID, sex, birthday of all patients diagnosed with 'RA' that are within the UN normal index.
column6: within the UN normal index refers to UN < 30; Diagnosis = 'RA'
column7: SELECT DISTINCT T1.ID, T1.SEX, T1.Birthday FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.UN < 30 AND T1.Diagnosis = 'RA'

column5: How many male patients are are with creatinine index out of the normal range?
column6: creatinine (CRE) out of the normal range refers to CRE > = 1.5; Male refers to Sex = 'M'
column7: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.CRE >= 1.5 AND T1.SEX = 'M'

column5: Are there more male patients with creatinine not within the normal range than female? True or False?
column6: creatinine (CRE) not within the normal range refers to CRE > = 1.5; male refers to Sex = 'M'; female refers to Sex = 'F'; calculation = (SUM(SEX = 'M') > SUM(SEX = 'F')) where CRE > = 1.5
column7: SELECT CASE WHEN SUM(CASE WHEN T1.SEX = 'M' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) > SUM(CASE WHEN T1.SEX = 'F' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) THEN 'True' ELSE 'False' END FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.CRE >= 1.5

column5: What is the highest total bilirubin level recorded? List out the patient details with ID, sex and birthday with that index.
column6: the highest total bilirubin refers to MAX(T-BIL)
column7: SELECT T2.`T-BIL`, T1.ID, T1.SEX, T1.Birthday FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID ORDER BY T2.`T-BIL` DESC LIMIT 1

column5: List and group all patients by sex for total bilirubin (T-BIL) level not within the normal range.
column6: List refers to GROUP_CONCAT(DISTINCT ID); total bilirubin (T-BIL) not within normal range refers to T-BIL > = 2.0
column7: SELECT T1.ID,T1.SEX FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.`T-BIL` >= 2.0 GROUP BY T1.SEX,T1.ID

column5: Who is the oldest patient with the highest total cholesterol (T-CHO). State the patient ID and T-CHO index.
column6: oldest patient refers to MIN(birthday); highest total cholesterol refers to MAX(T-CHO);
column7: SELECT T1.ID, T2.`T-CHO` FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID ORDER BY T2.`T-CHO` DESC, T1.Birthday ASC LIMIT 1

column5: What is the average age of the male patient with high cholesterol?
column6: average age = DIVIDE(SUM(SUBTRACT(YEAR(NOW()), YEAR(birthday))), COUNT(ID)); male patient refers to sex = 'M'; high cholesterol refers to `T-CHO` > = 250;
column7: SELECT AVG(STRFTIME('%Y', date('NOW')) - STRFTIME('%Y', T1.Birthday)) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.`T-CHO` >= 250 AND T1.SEX = 'M'

column5: Provide list of patients and their diagnosis with triglyceride (TG) index greater than 100 of the normal range?
column6: triglyceride (TG) index greater than 100 of the normal range refers to TG > 300;
column7: SELECT T1.ID, T1.Diagnosis FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.TG > 300

column5: For all patients with triglyceride (TG) level beyond the normal range, how many are age more than 50 years?
column6: triglyceride (TG) level beyond the normal range refers to TG > = 200; more than 50 years of age = SUBTRACT(year(current_timestamp), year(Birthday)) > 50; Should consider DISTINCT in the final result;
column7: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.TG >= 200 AND STRFTIME('%Y', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP) - STRFTIME('%Y', T1.Birthday) > 50

column5: List all outpatient within normal range of creatinine phosphokinase. Give me the distinct ids.
column6: outpatient refers to Admission = '-'; normal range of creatinine phosphokinase refers to CPK < 250;
column7: SELECT DISTINCT T1.ID FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.CPK < 250 AND T1.Admission = '-'

column5: For patient born between 1936-1956, how many male patients have creatinine phosphokinase beyond the normal range?
column6: born between 1936-1956 refers to year(Birthday) BETWEEN '1936' AND '1956'; male patients refers to sex = 'M'; creatinine phosphokinase beyond the normal range refers to CPK > = 250; Should consider DISTINCT in the final result;
column7: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE STRFTIME('%Y', T1.Birthday) BETWEEN '1936' AND '1956' AND T1.SEX = 'M' AND T2.CPK >= 250

column5: Provide ID, sex and age of patient who has blood glucose (GLU) not within normal range but with total cholesterol(T-CHO) within normal range.
column6: age = SUBTRACT(year(current_timestamp), year(Birthday)); blood glucose (GLU) not within normal range refers to GLU > = 180; total cholesterol(T-CHO) within normal range refers to `T-CHO` < 250;
column7: SELECT DISTINCT T1.ID, T1.SEX , STRFTIME('%Y', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP) - STRFTIME('%Y', T1.Birthday) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.GLU >= 180 AND T2.`T-CHO` < 250

column5: List each patient's ID and blood glucose (GLU) index that were within normal range for patient's whose data was first recorded in 1991.
column6: blood glucose (GLU) index that were within normal range refers to GLU < 180; data that was first recorded in 1991 refers to year(Description) = 1991;
column7: SELECT DISTINCT T1.ID, T2.GLU FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE STRFTIME('%Y', T1.`First Date`) = '1991' AND T2.GLU < 180

column5: List the patient ID, sex and birthday who has abnormal white blood cell count. Group them by sex and list the patient by age in ascending order.
column6: abnormal white blood cell count refers to WBC < = 3.5 or WBC > = 9.0;
column7: SELECT DISTINCT T1.ID, T1.SEX, T1.Birthday FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.WBC <= 3.5 OR T2.WBC >= 9.0 GROUP BY T1.SEX,T1.ID ORDER BY T1.Birthday ASC

column5: What are the patient's diagnosis for those who has lower red blood blood cell? State their ID and age.
column6: patient's diagnosis refers to Diagnosis; lower red blood cell refers to RBC < 3.5; age = SUBTRACT(year(current_timestamp), year(Birthday));
column7: SELECT DISTINCT T1.Diagnosis, T1.ID , STRFTIME('%Y', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP) -STRFTIME('%Y', T1.Birthday) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.RBC < 3.5

column5: For all the female patient age 50 and above, who has abnormal red blood cell count. State if they were admitted to hospital.
column6: female patient refers to Sex = 'F'; age 50 and above = SUBTRACT(year(current_timestamp), year(Birthday)) > = 50; abnormal red blood cell count refers to RBC < = 3.5 or RBC > = 6.0; Admission = '+' means the patient was admitted to the hospital; Admission = '-' means the patient was not admitted to the hospital;
column7: SELECT DISTINCT T1.ID, T1.Admission FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T1.SEX = 'F' AND (T2.RBC <= 3.5 OR T2.RBC >= 6.0) AND STRFTIME('%Y', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP) - STRFTIME('%Y', T1.Birthday) >= 50

column5: Among all outpatients, list out those have low hemoglobin level. State the different IDs and their sex.
column6: outpatients refers to Admission = '-'; low hemoglobin level refers to HBG < 10;
column7: SELECT DISTINCT T1.ID, T1.SEX FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.HGB < 10 AND T1.Admission = '-'

column5: Among the patients who were diagnosed with SLE, who is the oldest with normal hemoglobin level. Provide the ID and sex.
column6: diagnosed with SLE refers to Diagnosis = 'SLE'; The larger the birthday value, the younger the person is, and vice versa; normal hemoglobin level refers to 10 < HGB < 17;
column7: SELECT T1.ID, T1.SEX FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T1.Diagnosis = 'SLE' AND T2.HGB > 10 AND T2.HGB < 17 ORDER BY T1.Birthday ASC LIMIT 1

column5: Name the ID and age of patient with two or more laboratory examinations which show their hematoclit level exceeded the normal range.
column6: age = SUBTRACT(year(current_timestamp), year(Birthday)); patient with two or more laboratory examinations refers to COUNT(ID) > 2; hematoclit level exceeded the normal range refers to HCT > = 52;
column7: SELECT DISTINCT T1.ID, STRFTIME('%Y', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP) - STRFTIME('%Y', T1.Birthday) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T1.ID IN ( SELECT ID FROM Laboratory WHERE HCT >= 52 GROUP BY ID HAVING COUNT(ID) >= 2 )

column5: From laboratory examinations in 1991, what is the average hematoclit level that is lower than the normal range.
column6: laboratory examinations in 1991 refers to Date like '1991%'; average hematoclit level = AVG(HCT); hematoclit level that is lower than the normal range refers to HCT < 29;
column7: SELECT AVG(T2.HCT) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.HCT < 29 AND STRFTIME('%Y', T2.Date) = '1991'

column5: For patients with abnormal platelet level, state the number of patients with lower than normal range. How is it compare to the number of patients with higher than normal range?
column6: abnormal platelet level refers to PLT <= 100 or PLT >= 400; platelet level lower than normal range refers to PLT < 100; calculation = SUBTRACT(SUM(PLT < 100), SUM(PLT > 400)); platelet level higher than normal range refers to PLT > 400;
column7: SELECT SUM(CASE WHEN T2.PLT <= 100 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) - SUM(CASE WHEN T2.PLT >= 400 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID

column5: For laboratory examinations take in 1984, list all patients below 50 years old with normal platelet level.
column6: laboratory examinations take in 1984 refers to YEAR(Date) = '1984'; below 50 years old = SUBTRACT(year(current_timestamp), year(Birthday)) < 50; normal platelet level refers to PLT between 100 and 400;
column7: SELECT DISTINCT T1.ID FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.PLT BETWEEN 100 AND 400 AND STRFTIME('%Y', T2.Date) - STRFTIME('%Y', T1.Birthday) < 50 AND STRFTIME('%Y', T2.Date) = '1984'

column5: For all patients who are older than 55 years old, what is the percentage of female who has abnormal prothrombin time (PT)?
column6: older than 55 years old = SUBTRACT(year(current_timestamp), year(Birthday)) > 55; abnormal prothrombin time (PT) refers to PT > = 14; percentage = DIVIDE(SUM(PT > = 14 AND SEX = 'F'), SUM(PT > = 14)) * 100; female refers to sex = 'F';
column7: SELECT CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN T2.PT >= 14 AND T1.SEX = 'F' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) * 100 / COUNT(*) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE STRFTIME('%Y', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP) - STRFTIME('%Y', T1.Birthday) > 55

column5: List all patients who first came to the hospital after year 1992 with prothrombin time (PT) level that are normal.
column6: first came to the hospital after year 1992 refers to year(`First Date`) > 1992; prothrombin time (PT) level that are normal refers to PT < 14;
column7: SELECT T1.ID FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE STRFTIME('%Y', T1.`First Date`) > '1992' AND T2.PT < 14

column5: For the examinations done after 1997/1/1, how many of them have the result of an inactivated partial prothrom bin time?
column6: examinations done after 1997/1/1 refers to `Examination Date` > '1997-01-01'; normal activated partial prothrom bin time refesr to APTT < 45;
column7: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.Date > '1997-01-01' AND T2.APTT >= 45

column5: For the patients with an abnormal activated partial prothrom bin time, how many of them does not have thrombosis?
column6: abnormal activated partial prothrom bin time refers to APTT > 45; does not have thrombosis refers to Thrombosis = 0; Only count ones without repetitive.
column7: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID INNER JOIN Examination AS T3 ON T3.ID = T2.ID WHERE T3.Thrombosis = 0 AND T2.APTT > 45

column5: Among the male patients who have a normal level of white blood cells, how many of them have an abnormal fibrinogen level?
column6: male patients refers to Sex = 'M'; normal level of white blood cells refers to WBC > 3.5 and WBC <9.0; abnormal fibrinogen level refers to FG < = 150 or FG > = 450; Don't compute repetitive ones.
column7: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.FG <= 150 OR T2.FG >= 450 AND T2.WBC > 3.5 AND T2.WBC < 9.0 AND T1.SEX = 'M'

column5: How many patients born after 1980/1/1 have an abnormal fibrinogen level?
column6: born after 1980/1/1 refers to Birthday > '1980-01-01'; normal fibrinogen level refers to FG between 150 and 450; Should return the number of distinct patients.
column7: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.FG <= 150 OR T2.FG >= 450 AND T1.Birthday > '1980-01-01'

column5: Please list the disease names of the patients that have a proteinuria level higher than normal.
column6: disease names refers to Diagnosis; proteinuria level higher than normal refers to `U-PRO` > = 30;
column7: SELECT T1.Diagnosis FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.`U-PRO` >= 30

column5: Which patient has a normal proteinuria level and is diagnosed with SLE? Please give his or her patient ID.
column6: normal proteinuria level refers to 0 < `U-PRO` < 30; diagnosed with SLE refers to Diagnosis = 'SLE';
column7: SELECT DISTINCT T1.ID FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.`U-PRO` > 0 AND T2.`U-PRO` < 30 AND T1.Diagnosis = 'SLE'

column5: How many patients with an Ig G higher than normal?
column6: Ig G higher than normal refers to IGG >= 2000; Should consider DISTINCT in the final result;
column7: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID INNER JOIN Examination AS T3 ON T3.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.IGG >= 2000

column5: Among the patients with a normal Ig G level, how many of them have symptoms?
column6: normal Ig G level refers to IGG > 900 and IGG < 2000; have symptoms refers to Symptoms IS NOT NULL;
column7: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID INNER JOIN Examination AS T3 ON T3.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.IGG BETWEEN 900 AND 2000 AND T3.Symptoms IS NOT NULL

column5: How many patients with a normal Ig A level came to the hospital after 1990/1/1?
column6: normal Ig A level refers to IGA > 80 AND IGA < 500; came to the hospital after 1990/1/1 refers to YEAR(`First Date`) > = 1990;
column7: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.IGA BETWEEN 80 AND 500 AND  strftime('%Y',  T1.`First Date`) > '1990'

column5: For the patients with an abnormal Ig M level, what is the most common disease they are diagnosed with?
column6: abnormal Ig M level refers to IGM <=40 OR IGM >= 400; most common disease refers to MAX(COUNT(Diagnosis));
column7: SELECT T1.Diagnosis FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.IGM NOT BETWEEN 40 AND 400 GROUP BY T1.Diagnosis ORDER BY COUNT(T1.Diagnosis) DESC LIMIT 1

column5: How many patients with a abnormal C-reactive protein don't have their data recorded?
column6: abnormal C-reactive protein refers to CRP ='+'; don't have data recorded refers to Description IS NULL;
column7: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE (T2.CRP = '+' ) AND T1.Description IS NULL

column5: Among the patients whose creatinine level is abnormal, how many of them aren't 70 yet?
column6: creatinine level is abnormal refers to CRE >= 1.5; aren't 70 yet refers to SUBTRACT((YEAR(CURDATE()), YEAR(Birthday))) < 70;
column7: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.CRE >= 1.5 AND STRFTIME('%Y', Date('now')) - STRFTIME('%Y', T1.Birthday) < 70

column5: How many patients with a normal Rhuematoid Factor has a positive measure of degree of coagulation?
column6: normal Rhuematoid Factor refers TO RA IN('-', '+-'); positive measure of degree of coagulation refers to KCT = '+'; Should compute the number of distinct ones
column7: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID INNER JOIN Examination AS T3 ON T3.ID = T2.ID WHERE (T2.RA = '-' OR T2.RA = '+-') AND T3.KCT = '+'

column5: Please list the diseases of the patients born after 1985-1-1 and have a normal Rhuematoid Factor.
column6: diseases refers to Diagnosis; born after 1985/1/1 refers to YEAR(Birthday) > = 1985; normal Rhuematoid Factor refers to RA IN('-', '+-');
column7: SELECT T1.Diagnosis FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE (T2.RA = '-' OR T2.RA = '+-') AND T1.Birthday > '1985-01-01'

column5: Please list the ID of the patient whose RF is normal and who is older than 60.
column6: RF is normal refers to RF < 20; older than 60 = SUBTRACT((YEAR(CURDATE()), YEAR(Birthday))) > 60;
column7: SELECT T1.ID FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.RF < 20 AND STRFTIME('%Y', DATE('now')) - STRFTIME('%Y', T1.Birthday) > 60

column5: How many patients with a normal RF don't have thrombosis?
column6: normal RF refers to RF < 20; don't have thrombosis refers to Thrombosis = '0';
column7: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.ID) FROM Examination AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.RF < 20 AND T1.Thrombosis = 0

column5: How many patients with a normal level of complement 3 have a P pattern observed in the sheet of ANA examination?
column6: normal level of complement 3 refers to C3 > 35; have a P pattern observed in the sheet of ANA examination refers to ANA Pattern = 'P'; Should compute the number of distinct ones
column7: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.ID) FROM Examination AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.C3 > 35 AND T1.`ANA Pattern` = 'P'

column5: Among the patients whose level of Hematoclit isn't normal, which patient has the highest anti-Cardiolipin antibody concentration? Please list his or her ID.
column6: Hematoclit is normal refers to 29 < N < 52; highest anti-Cardiolipin antibody concentration refers to MAX(`aCL IgA`);
column7: SELECT DISTINCT T1.ID FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Examination AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T3 on T1.ID = T3.ID WHERE (T3.HCT >= 52 OR T3.HCT <= 29) ORDER BY T2.`aCL IgA` DESC LIMIT 1

column5: Among the patients have blood clots in veins, how many of them have a normal level of complement 4?
column6: APS will result in Blood Clots in veins; normal level of complement 4 refers to C4 > 10; Should compute the number of different ones
column7: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.C4 > 10 AND T1.Diagnosis = 'APS'

column5: How many patients have a normal level of anti-ribonuclear protein and have been admitted to the hospital?
column6: normal level of anti-ribonuclear protein refers to RNP = '-', '+-'; And'-' means 'negative'; '+-' refers to '0'; admitted to the hospital refers to Admission = '+'; Should consider DISTINCT in the final result;
column7: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.RNP = 'negative' OR T2.RNP = '0' AND T1.Admission = '+'

column5: Which is the youngest patient with an abnormal anti-ribonuclear protein level? Please list his or her date of birth.
column6: youngest patient refers to MAX(Birthday); abnormal anti-ribonuclear protein level refers to RNP NOT IN('-', '+-'); date of birth refers to Birthday;
column7: SELECT T1.Birthday FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.RNP != '-' OR '+-' ORDER BY T1.Birthday DESC LIMIT 1

column5: Among the patients with normal anti-SM, how many of them does not have thrombosis?
column6: normal anti-SM refers to SM IN('-', '+-'); SM = 'negative' means '-'; SM = '0' means '+-'; SM = '1' means '+'; does not have thrombosis refers to Thrombosis = 0;
column7: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Examination AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.SM IN ('negative','0') AND T1.Thrombosis = 0

column5: For the patients with an abnormal anti-SM, please list the IDs of the three youngest ones.
column6: abnormal anti-SM refers to SM NOT IN ('negative', '0'); youngest refers to MAX(Birthday);
column7: SELECT T1.ID FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.SM NOT IN ('negative','0') ORDER BY T1.Birthday DESC LIMIT 3

column5: Please list the IDs of the patients who had the examination done after 1997/1/1 and had a normal anti-scl70.
column6: examination done after 1997/1/1 refers to `Examination Date` >  1997-01-01; normal anti-scl70 refers to SC170 IN('negative','0');
column7: SELECT T1.ID FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.SC170 IN ('negative','0') AND T2.Date > 1997-01-01

column5: Among the patients who has a normal anti-scl70, how many of them are female and does not have any symptom?
column6: normal anti-scl70 refers to SC170 IN('negative', '0'); female refers to Sex = 'F'; does not have any symptom refers to symptoms IS NULL; Should consider DISTINCT in the final result;
column7: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID INNER JOIN Examination AS T3 ON T3.ID = T2.ID WHERE (T2.SC170 = 'negative' OR T2.SC170 = '0') AND T1.SEX = 'F' AND T3.Symptoms IS NULL

column5: How many patients with a normal anti-SSA came to the hospital before 2000?
column6: normal anti-SSA refers to SSA IN('-','+-'); came to the hospital before 2000 refers to YEAR(`First Date`) < 2000; Should compute the number of distinct ones
column7: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.SSA IN ('negative', '0') AND STRFTIME('%Y', T2.Date) < '2000'

column5: Which patient is the first patient with an abnormal anti-SSA to come to the hospital? Please give his or her ID.
column6: first patient refers to ID with MIN(`First Date`); abnormal anti-SSA refers to SSA NOT IN('negative', '0');
column7: SELECT T1.ID FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T1.`First Date` IS NOT NULL AND T2.SSA NOT IN ('negative', '0') ORDER BY T1.`First Date` ASC LIMIT 1

column5: How many patients have a normal anti-SSB and are diagnosed with SLE in the examination?
column6: normal anti-SSB refers to SSB IN('-', '+-'); '-' is expressed as 'negative' and '+-' is expressed as '0' in the database ; diagnosed with SLE refers to Diagnosis = 'SLE'; Should compute the number of distinct ones
column7: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.SSB = 'negative' OR '0' AND T1.Diagnosis = 'SLE'

column5: For the patients whose anti-SSB are normal, how many of them have other symptoms observed in their examination?
column6: anti-SSB are normal refers to SSB IN ('negative', '0'); have other symptoms refers to Symptoms IS NOT NULL; Should compute the number of distinct ones
column7: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.ID) FROM Examination AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.SSB = 'negative' OR '0' AND T1.Symptoms IS NOT NULL

column5: Among the patients who has a normal level of anti-centromere and a normal level of anti-SSB, how many of them are male?
column6: normal level of anti-centromere refers to CENTROMEA IN('-', '+-'); normal level of anti-SSB refers to SSB IN('-', '+-'); male refers to Sex = 'M'; Should consider DISTINCT in the final result;
column7: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.CENTROMEA IN ('negative', '0') AND T2.SSB IN ('negative', '0') AND T1.SEX = 'M'

column5: For the patients who have an abnormal level of anti-DNA, please list the diseases they are diagnosed with.
column6: abnormal level of anti-DNA refers to DNA > = 8; diseases refers to Diagnosis;
column7: SELECT DISTINCT(T1.Diagnosis) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.DNA >= 8

column5: How many patients have a normal anti-DNA level, yet their data are not recorded.
column6: normal anti-DNA level refers to DNA < 8; data are not recorded refers to Description IS NULL; Should compute the number of unique ones
column7: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.DNA < 8 AND T1.Description IS NULL

column5: Of the patients with an normal level of IGG, how many of them admitted to the hospital?
column6: normal level of IGG refers to 900 < IGG < 2000; admitted to the hospital refers to Admission = '+';
column7: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.IGG > 900 AND T2.IGG <2000 AND  T1.Admission = '+'

column5: What is the percentage of patient who has a abnormal level of glutamic oxaloacetic transaminase level, yet he or she is diagnosed with SLE?
column6: abnormal level of glutamic oxaloacetic transaminase refers to GOT > = 60; percentage = MULTIPLY(DIVIDE(COUNT(ID WHERE GOT > = 60 AND Diagnosis = 'SLE'), COUNT(ID WHERE GOT > = 60)), 1.0);
column7: SELECT COUNT(CASE WHEN T1.Diagnosis LIKE '%SLE%' THEN T1.ID ELSE 0 END) / COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.`GOT` >= 60

column5: How many male patients have their glutamic oxaloacetic transaminase in the normal range?
column6: male refers to Sex = 'M'; glutamic oxaloacetic transaminase in the normal range refers to GOT < 60;
column7: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.GOT < 60 AND T1.SEX = 'M'

column5: Among the patients who have an abnormal level of glutamic oxaloacetic transaminase, when was the youngest of them born?
column6: abnormal level of glutamic oxaloacetic transaminase refers to GOT > = 60; The larger the birthday value, the younger the person is, and vice versa;
column7: SELECT T1.Birthday FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.GOT >= 60 ORDER BY T1.Birthday DESC LIMIT 1

column5: Please list the top three patients' birthdays with the highest glutamic pylvic transaminase in the normal range.
column6: highest glutamic pylvic transaminase in the normal range refers to MAX(GPT < 60);
column7: SELECT T1.Birthday FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.GPT < 60 ORDER BY T2.GPT DESC LIMIT 3

column5: For the patients with the normal glutamic pylvic transaminase level, how many of them are male?
column6: normal glutamic pylvic transaminase level refers to GOT < 60; male refers to Sex = 'M';
column7: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.GOT < 60 AND T1.SEX = 'M'

column5: For the patient with the highest lactate dehydrogenase in the normal range, when was his or her data first recorded?
column6: highest lactate dehydrogenase in the normal range refers to MAX(LDH < 500); when the data first recorded refers to MIN(First Date);
column7: SELECT T1.`First Date` FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.LDH < 500 ORDER BY T2.LDH ASC LIMIT 1

column5: When is the latest patient's medical data recorded? This patient should have an abnormal level of lactate dehydrogenase.
column6: latest patient refers to ID with MAX('First Date'); abnormal level of lactate dehydrogenase refers to LDH > = 500;
column7: SELECT T1.`First Date` FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.LDH >= 500 ORDER BY T1.`First Date` DESC LIMIT 1

column5: For the patient with an abnormal alkaliphophatase level, how many of them are admitted to the hospital?
column6: abnormal alkaliphophatase level refers to ALP > = 300; admitted to the hospital refers to Admission = '+';
column7: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.ALP >= 300 AND T1.Admission = '+'
