column5: Among the patients followed at the outpatient clinic, how many of them have a normal level of alkaliphophatase?
column6: followed at the outpatient clinic refers to Admission = '-'; normal level of alkaliphophatase refers to ALP < 300;
column7: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.ALP < 300 AND T1.Admission = '-'

column5: Please list the diagnosis of the patients whose total protein is lower than normal.
column6: total protein is lower than normal refers to TP < 6.0;
column7: SELECT T1.Diagnosis FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.TP < 6.0

column5: For the patients who are diagnosed with SJS, how many of them have a normal level of total protein?
column6: diagnosed with SJS refers to Diagnosis = 'SJS'; normal level of total protein refers to TP > 6.0 and TP < 8.5;
column7: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T1.Diagnosis = 'SJS' AND T2.TP > 6.0 AND T2.TP < 8.5

column5: How many male patients have a normal level of both albumin and total protein?
column6: male refers to Sex = 'M'; normal level of both albumin and total protein refers to ALB > 3.5 and ALB < 5.5 AND TP between 6.0 and 8.5;
column7: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T1.SEX = 'M'  AND T2.ALB > 3.5 AND T2.ALB < 5.5 AND T2.TP BETWEEN 6.0 AND 8.5

column5: What is the anti Cardiolipin antibody concentration of the female patient with the highest uric acid level in the normal range?
column6: anti Cardiolipin antibody concentration refers to `aCL IgG`, `aCL IgM`, `aCL IgA`; female patient refers to Sex = F'; highest uric acid level in the normal range refers to MAX(UA > 6.50);
column7: SELECT T3.`aCL IgG`, T3.`aCL IgM`, T3.`aCL IgA` FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID INNER JOIN Examination AS T3 ON T3.ID = T2.ID WHERE T1.SEX = 'F' AND T2.UA > 6.5 ORDER BY T2.UA DESC LIMIT 1

column5: What is the highest anti-nucleus antibody concentration level of a patient with a normal creatinine level?
column6: highest anti-nucleus antibody concentration level refers to MAX(ANA); normal creatinine level refers to CRE < 1.5;
column7: SELECT T2.ANA FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Examination AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T3 ON T1.ID = T3.ID WHERE T3.CRE < 1.5 ORDER BY T2.ANA DESC LIMIT 1

column5: Please list the patient's ID whose creatinine level is normal and whose anti Cardiolipin antibody concentration level is the highest.
column6: creatinine level is normal refers to CRE < 1.5; anti Cardiolipin antibody concentration level is the highest refers to MAX(aCL IgA);
column7: SELECT T2.ID FROM Laboratory AS T1 INNER JOIN Examination AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T1.CRE < 1.5 ORDER BY T2.`aCL IgA` DESC LIMIT 1

column5: Among the patients whose total bilirubin is over the normal range, how many of them have a peripheral pattern observed in the sheet of ANA examination?
column6: total bilirubin is over the normal range refers to `T-BIL` > = 2.0; peripheral pattern is observed in the sheet of ANA examination refers to that ANA Pattern contains 'P';
column7: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID INNER JOIN Examination AS T3 ON T1.ID = T3.ID WHERE T2.`T-BIL` >= 2 AND T3.`ANA Pattern` LIKE '%P%'

column5: What is the anti-nucleus antibody concentration of the patient whose total bilirubin is the highest in the normal range?
column6: anti-nucleus antibody concentration refers to ANA; total bilirubin is the highest in the normal range refers to MAX(`T-BIL` < 2.0);
column7: SELECT T3.ANA FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID INNER JOIN Examination AS T3 ON T1.ID = T3.ID WHERE T2.`T-BIL` < 2.0 ORDER BY T2.`T-BIL` DESC LIMIT 1

column5: For the patients whose total cholesterol is higher than normal, how many of them have a negative measure of degree of coagulation?
column6: total cholesterol is higher than normal refers to `T-CHO` > = 250; negative measure of degree of coagulation refers to KCT = '-' ;
column7: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID INNER JOIN Examination AS T3 ON T1.ID = T3.ID WHERE T2.`T-CHO` >= 250 AND T3.KCT = '-'

column5: Among the patients whose total cholesterol is within the normal range, how many of them have a P pattern observed in the sheet of ANA examination?
column6: total cholesterol is within the normal range refers to `T-CHO` < 250; P pattern observed in the sheet of ANA examination refers to ANA Pattern = 'P';
column7: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID INNER JOIN Examination AS T3 ON T1.ID = T3.ID WHERE T3.`ANA Pattern` = 'P' AND T2.`T-CHO` < 250

column5: Among the patients with the normal level of triglyceride, how many of them have other symptoms observed?
column6: normal level of triglyceride refers to TG < 200; have other symptoms refers to Symptoms is not null;
column7: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Examination AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.TG < 200 AND T1.Symptoms IS NOT NULL

column5: What is the disease name of the patient who has the highest level of triglyceride within the normal range?
column6: disease name referse to Diagnosis; highest level of triglyceride within the normal range refers to MAX(TG < 200);
column7: SELECT T1.Diagnosis FROM Examination AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.TG < 200 ORDER BY T2.TG DESC LIMIT 1

column5: Please list the IDs of the patients with no thrombosis and an abnormal level of creatinine phosphokinase.
column6: no thrombosis refers to Thrombosis = 0 ; abnormal level of creatinine phosphokinase refers to CPK < 250;
column7: SELECT DISTINCT T1.ID FROM Laboratory AS T1 INNER JOIN Examination AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.Thrombosis = 0 AND T1.CPK < 250

column5: For the patients with a normal range of creatinine phosphokinase, how many of them have a positive measure of degree of coagulation?
column6: normal range of creatinine phosphokinase refers to CPK < 250; positive measure of degree of coagulation refers to KCT = '+' or RVVT = '+' or LAC = '+' ;
column7: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID INNER JOIN Examination AS T3 ON T1.ID = T3.ID WHERE T2.CPK < 250 AND (T3.KCT = '+' OR T3.RVVT = '+' OR T3.LAC = '+')

column5: When is the birthday of the oldest patient whose blood glucose is abnormal?
column6: oldest patient refers to MIN(Birthday); blood glucose is abnormal refers to GLU > 180;
column7: SELECT T1.Birthday FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.GLU > 180 ORDER BY T1.Birthday ASC LIMIT 1

column5: Among the patients with a normal blood glucose, how many of them don't have thrombosis?
column6: normal blood glucose refers to GLU < 180; don't have thrombosis refers to Thrombosis = 0;
column7: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID INNER JOIN Examination AS T3 ON T1.ID = T3.ID WHERE T2.GLU < 180 AND T3.Thrombosis = 0

column5: How many patients accepted to the hospital have a normal level of white blood cells?
column6: accepted to the hospital refers to Admission = '+'; normal level of white blood cells refers to WBC between 3.5 and 9.0;
column7: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.WBC BETWEEN 3.5 AND 9 AND T1.Admission = '+'

column5: How many patients diagnosed with SLE have a normal white blood cell level?
column6: diagnosed with SLE refers to Diagnosis = 'SLE'; normal white blood cell level refers to WBC between 3.5 and 9.0;
column7: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T1.Diagnosis = 'SLE' AND T2.WBC BETWEEN 3.5 AND 9

column5: Please list the patient's ID if he or she has an abnormal level of red blood cell and is followed at the outpatient clinic.
column6: RBC < = 3.5 or RBC > = 6.0 means the patient has an abnormal level of red blood cell; 3.5 < RBC < 6.0 means the patient has a normal level of red blood cell; followed at the outpatient clinic refers to Admission = '-';
column7: SELECT DISTINCT T1.ID FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE (T2.RBC <= 3.5 OR T2.RBC >= 6) AND T1.Admission = '-'

column5: Among the patients who have a normal platelet level, how many of them have other symptoms observed?
column6: normal platelet level refers to PLT > 100 and PLT < 400; have other symptoms refers to Diagnosis is not null;
column7: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.PLT > 100 AND T2.PLT < 400 AND T1.Diagnosis IS NOT NULL

column5: Please list a patient's platelet level if it is within the normal range and if he or she is diagnosed with MCTD.
column6: PLT > 100 and PLT < 400 means platelet level is within the normal range; PLT < 100 and PLT > 400 means platelet level is not within the normal range; diagnosed with MCTD refers to Diagnosis = 'MCTD';
column7: SELECT T2.PLT FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T1.Diagnosis = 'MCTD' AND T2.PLT BETWEEN 100 AND 400

column5: For the male patients that have a normal prothrombin time, what is their average prothrombin time?
column6: male refers to Sex = 'M'; normal prothrombin time refer to PT < 14; average prothrombin time = AVG(PT);
column7: SELECT AVG(T2.PT) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.PT < 14 AND T1.SEX = 'M'

column5: How many patients with severe thrombosis have a normal prothrombin time?
column6: severe thrombosis refers to Thrombosis = 2 or 1; normal prothrombin time refers to PT < 14;
column7: SELECT COUNT(T1.ID) FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID INNER JOIN Examination AS T3 ON T1.ID = T3.ID WHERE T2.PT < 14 AND T3.Thrombosis < 3 AND T3.Thrombosis > 0

column5: What's Angela Sanders's major?
column6: Angela Sanders is the full name; full name refers to first_name, last_name; major refers to major_name.
column7: SELECT T2.major_name FROM member AS T1 INNER JOIN major AS T2 ON T1.link_to_major = T2.major_id WHERE T1.first_name = 'Angela' AND T1.last_name = 'Sanders'

column5: How many students in the Student_Club are from the College of Engineering?
column7: SELECT COUNT(T1.member_id) FROM member AS T1 INNER JOIN major AS T2 ON T1.link_to_major = T2.major_id WHERE T2.college = 'College of Engineering'

column5: Please list the full names of the students in the Student_Club that come from the Art and Design Department.
column6: full name refers to first_name, last_name;
column7: SELECT T1.first_name, T1.last_name FROM member AS T1 INNER JOIN major AS T2 ON T1.link_to_major = T2.major_id WHERE T2.department = 'Art and Design Department'

column5: How many students of the Student_Club have attended the event "Women's Soccer"?
column6: Women's Soccer is an event name
column7: SELECT COUNT(T1.event_id) FROM event AS T1 INNER JOIN attendance AS T2 ON T1.event_id = T2.link_to_event WHERE T1.event_name = 'Women''s Soccer'

column5: Please list the phone numbers of the students from the Student_Club that has attended the event "Women's Soccer".
column6: Women's Soccer is an event name; phone numbers refers to phone
column7: SELECT T3.phone FROM event AS T1 INNER JOIN attendance AS T2 ON T1.event_id = T2.link_to_event INNER JOIN member AS T3 ON T2.link_to_member = T3.member_id WHERE T1.event_name = 'Women''s Soccer'

column5: Among the students from the Student_Club who attended the event "Women's Soccer", how many of them want a T-shirt that's in medium size?
column6: Women's Soccer is an event name; T-shirt that is in medium size refers to t_shirt_size = 'Medium'
column7: SELECT COUNT(T1.event_id) FROM event AS T1 INNER JOIN attendance AS T2 ON T1.event_id = T2.link_to_event INNER JOIN member AS T3 ON T2.link_to_member = T3.member_id WHERE T1.event_name = 'Women''s Soccer' AND T3.t_shirt_size = 'Medium'

column5: What is the event that has the highest attendance of the students from the Student_Club?
column6: event with highest attendance refers to MAX(COUNT(link_to_event))
column7: SELECT T1.event_name FROM event AS T1 INNER JOIN attendance AS T2 ON T1.event_id = T2.link_to_event GROUP BY T1.event_name ORDER BY COUNT(T2.link_to_event) DESC LIMIT 1

column5: Which college is the vice president of the Student_Club from?
column6: Vice President is a position of the Student Club
column7: SELECT T2.college FROM member AS T1 INNER JOIN major AS T2 ON T1.link_to_major = T2.major_id WHERE T1.position LIKE 'vice president'

column5: Please list the event names of all the events attended by Maya Mclean.
column7: SELECT T1.event_name FROM event AS T1 INNER JOIN attendance AS T2 ON T1.event_id = T2.link_to_event INNER JOIN member AS T3 ON T2.link_to_member = T3.member_id WHERE T3.first_name = 'Maya' AND T3.last_name = 'Mclean'

column5: How many events of the Student_Club did Sacha Harrison attend in 2019?
column6: events attended in 2019 refers to YEAR(event_date) = 2019
column7: SELECT COUNT(T1.event_id) FROM event AS T1 INNER JOIN attendance AS T2 ON T1.event_id = T2.link_to_event INNER JOIN member AS T3 ON T2.link_to_member = T3.member_id WHERE T3.first_name = 'Sacha' AND T3.last_name = 'Harrison' AND SUBSTR(T1.event_date, 1, 4) = '2019'

column5: Among the events attended by more than 10 members of the Student_Club, how many of them are meetings?
column6: meetings events refers to type = 'Meeting'; attended by more than 10 members refers to COUNT(event_id) > 10
column7: SELECT T1.event_name FROM event AS T1  INNER JOIN attendance AS T2 ON T1.event_id = T2.link_to_event GROUP BY T1.event_id  HAVING COUNT(T2.link_to_event) > 10 EXCEPT SELECT T1.event_name  FROM event AS T1  WHERE T1.type = 'Meeting'

column5: List all the names of events that had an attendance of over 20 students but were not fundraisers.
column6: name of events refers to event_name; attendance of over 20 students COUNT(event_id) > 20.
column7: SELECT T1.event_name FROM event AS T1 INNER JOIN attendance AS T2 ON T1.event_id = T2.link_to_event GROUP BY T1.event_id HAVING COUNT(T2.link_to_event) > 20 EXCEPT SELECT T1.event_name FROM event AS T1  WHERE T1.type = 'Fundraiser'

column5: What is the average attendance of meetings in 2020?
column6: meetings in 2020 refers to type = 'Meeting' where YEAR(event_date) = 2020; average = DIVIDE(COUNT(event_id), COUNT(DISTINCT event_name))
column7: SELECT CAST(COUNT(T2.link_to_event) AS REAL) / COUNT(DISTINCT T2.link_to_event) FROM event AS T1 INNER JOIN attendance AS T2 ON T1.event_id = T2.link_to_event WHERE SUBSTR(T1.event_date, 1, 4) = '2020' AND T1.type = 'Meeting'

column5: How many members of the Student_Club have majored Environmental Engineering?
column6: Environmental Engineering' is the major name
column7: SELECT COUNT(T1.member_id) FROM member AS T1 INNER JOIN major AS T2 ON T1.link_to_major = T2.major_id WHERE T2.major_name = 'Environmental Engineering'

column5: List the full name of all the members of the Student_Club who attended the "Laugh Out Loud" event.
column6: full name of members refers to first_name, last_name; 'Laugh Out Loud' is an event name;
column7: SELECT T1.first_name, T1.last_name FROM member AS T1 INNER JOIN attendance AS T2 ON T1.member_id = T2.link_to_member INNER JOIN event AS T3 ON T2.link_to_event = T3.event_id WHERE T3.event_name = 'Laugh Out Loud'

column5: List the last name of all the students who majored Law and Constitutional Studies.
column6: Law and Constitutional Studies' is the major name
column7: SELECT T1.last_name FROM member AS T1 INNER JOIN major AS T2 ON T1.link_to_major = T2.major_id WHERE T2.major_name = 'Law and Constitutional Studies'

column5: What county did Sherri Ramsey grew up?
column7: SELECT T2.county FROM member AS T1 INNER JOIN zip_code AS T2 ON T1.zip = T2.zip_code WHERE T1.first_name = 'Sherri' AND T1.last_name = 'Ramsey'

column5: What college offers the major that Tyler Hewitt took?
column7: SELECT T2.college FROM member AS T1 INNER JOIN major AS T2 ON T1.link_to_major = T2.major_id WHERE T1.first_name = 'Tyler' AND T1.last_name = 'Hewitt'

column5: What is the amount of the funds that the Vice President received?
column6: Vice President' is a position of Student Club; funds received refers to amount.
column7: SELECT T2.amount FROM member AS T1 INNER JOIN income AS T2 ON T1.member_id = T2.link_to_member WHERE T1.position = 'Vice President'

column5: How much did the Student_Club members spend on food in September Meeting?
column6: amount spent refers to spent; spend on food in September Meeting refers to category = 'Food' where event_name = 'September Meeting'
column7: SELECT T2.spent FROM event AS T1 INNER JOIN budget AS T2 ON T1.event_id = T2.link_to_event WHERE T1.event_name = 'September Meeting' AND T2.category = 'Food' AND SUBSTR(T1.event_date, 6, 2) = '09'

column5: What city and state did the President of the Student_Club grow up?
column6: President' is a position of Student Club;
column7: SELECT T2.city, T2.state FROM member AS T1 INNER JOIN zip_code AS T2 ON T1.zip = T2.zip_code WHERE T1.position = 'President'

column5: List the full name of the Student_Club members that grew up in Illinois state.
column6: full name of member refers to first_name, last_name
column7: SELECT T1.first_name, T1.last_name FROM member AS T1 INNER JOIN zip_code AS T2 ON T1.zip = T2.zip_code WHERE T2.state = 'Illinois'

column5: How much did the Student_Club members spend on advertisement in September Meeting?
column6: amount spent refers to spent; spend on food in September Meeting refers to category = 'Advertisement' where event_name = 'September Meeting'
column7: SELECT T2.spent FROM event AS T1 INNER JOIN budget AS T2 ON T1.event_id = T2.link_to_event WHERE T1.event_name = 'September Meeting' AND T2.category = 'Advertisement' AND SUBSTR(T1.event_date, 6, 2) = '09'

column5: What department offers the major that Pierce and Guidi took?
column7: SELECT T2.department FROM member AS T1 INNER JOIN major AS T2 ON T1.link_to_major = T2.major_id WHERE T1.last_name = 'Pierce' OR T1.last_name = 'Guidi'

column5: What is the total budgeted amount for all category in "October Speaker" event?
column6: total budgeted amount refers to SUM(amount) where event_name = 'October Speaker'
column7: SELECT SUM(T2.amount) FROM event AS T1 INNER JOIN budget AS T2 ON T1.event_id = T2.link_to_event WHERE T1.event_name = 'October Speaker'

column5: Was each expense in October Meeting on October 8, 2019 approved?
column6: event_name = 'October Meeting' where event_date = '2019-10-08'; approved = True means expenses was approved; approved = False means expenses was not approved
column7: SELECT T3.approved FROM event AS T1 INNER JOIN budget AS T2 ON T1.event_id = T2.link_to_event INNER JOIN expense AS T3 ON T2.budget_id = T3.link_to_budget WHERE T1.event_name = 'October Meeting' AND T1.event_date LIKE '2019-10-08%'

column5: Calculate the total average cost that Elijah Allen spent in the events on September and October.
column6: Elijah Allen is the full name; full name refers to first_name, last_name; The 5th and 6th string of the expense_date in the expense table can refer to month; events in September and October refers to month(expense_date) = 9 OR month(expense_date) = 10
column7: SELECT AVG(T2.cost) FROM member AS T1 INNER JOIN expense AS T2 ON T1.member_id = T2.link_to_member WHERE T1.last_name = 'Allen' AND T1.first_name = 'Elijah' AND (SUBSTR(T2.expense_date, 6, 2) = '09' OR SUBSTR(T2.expense_date, 6, 2) = '10')

column5: Calculate the difference of the total amount spent in all events by the Student_Club in year 2019 and 2020.
column6: The first 4 strings of the event_date values in the event table can represent year; The difference of the total amount spent = SUBTRACT(spent where YEAR(event_date) = 2019, spent where YEAR(event_date) = 2020)
column7: SELECT SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTR(T1.event_date, 1, 4) = '2019' THEN T2.spent ELSE 0 END) - SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTR(T1.event_date, 1, 4) = '2020' THEN T2.spent ELSE 0 END) AS num FROM event AS T1 INNER JOIN budget AS T2 ON T1.event_id = T2.link_to_event

column5: Tell the hometown county for "Adela O'Gallagher".
column6: hometown county refers to county
column7: SELECT T2.county FROM member AS T1 INNER JOIN zip_code AS T2 ON T1.zip = T2.zip_code WHERE T1.first_name = 'Adela' AND T1.last_name = 'O''Gallagher'

column5: For all the budgets for "November Meeting", how many of them had exceeded the budget?
column6: November Meeting' is an event name; remaining < 0 means the cost had exceeded the budget
column7: SELECT COUNT(T2.event_id) FROM budget AS T1 INNER JOIN event AS T2 ON T1.link_to_event = T2.event_id WHERE T2.event_name = 'November Meeting' AND T1.remaining < 0

column5: Provide the total number of the budget amount for "September Speaker" event.
column6: September Speaker' is an event name; total number of budget amount refers to SUM(amount)
column7: SELECT SUM(T1.amount) FROM budget AS T1 INNER JOIN event AS T2 ON T1.link_to_event = T2.event_id WHERE T2.event_name = 'September Speaker'

column5: What is the status of the event which bought "Post Cards, Posters" on 2019/8/20?
column6: Post Cards, Posters' is an expense description; on 2019/8/20 refers to expense_date = '2019-8-20'; status of event refers to event_status
column7: SELECT T1.event_status FROM budget AS T1 INNER JOIN expense AS T2 ON T1.budget_id = T2.link_to_budget WHERE T2.expense_description = 'Post Cards, Posters' AND T2.expense_date = '2019-08-20'

column5: What was Brent Thomason's major?
column6: Brent Thomason is the full name; full name refers to first_name, last_name; major refers to major_name
column7: SELECT T2.major_name FROM member AS T1 INNER JOIN major AS T2 ON T1.link_to_major = T2.major_id WHERE T1.first_name = 'Brent' AND T1.last_name = 'Thomason'

column5: For all the club members from "Business" major, how many of them wear medium size t-shirt?
column6: Business' is a major name; wear medium size t-shirt refers to t_shirt_size = 'Medium'

column6: full name refers to first_name, last_name; major of members refers to major_name; spend more than a hundred dollars on an expense refers to cost > 100
