column5: Which professionals live in the state of Indiana or have done treatment on more than 2 treatments? List his or her id, last name and cell phone.
column7: SELECT professional_id ,  last_name ,  cell_number FROM Professionals WHERE state  =  'Indiana' UNION SELECT T1.professional_id ,  T1.last_name ,  T1.cell_number FROM Professionals AS T1 JOIN Treatments AS T2 ON T1.professional_id  =  T2.professional_id GROUP BY T1.professional_id HAVING count(*)  >  2

column5: Find the id, last name and cell phone of the professionals who live in the state of Indiana or have performed more than two treatments.
column7: SELECT professional_id ,  last_name ,  cell_number FROM Professionals WHERE state  =  'Indiana' UNION SELECT T1.professional_id ,  T1.last_name ,  T1.cell_number FROM Professionals AS T1 JOIN Treatments AS T2 ON T1.professional_id  =  T2.professional_id GROUP BY T1.professional_id HAVING count(*)  >  2

column5: Which professional did not operate any treatment on dogs? List the professional's id, role and email.
column7: SELECT professional_id ,  role_code ,  email_address FROM Professionals EXCEPT SELECT T1.professional_id ,  T1.role_code ,  T1.email_address FROM Professionals AS T1 JOIN Treatments AS T2 ON T1.professional_id  =  T2.professional_id

column5: Give me the id, role and email of the professionals who did not perform any treatment on dogs.
column7: SELECT professional_id ,  role_code ,  email_address FROM Professionals EXCEPT SELECT T1.professional_id ,  T1.role_code ,  T1.email_address FROM Professionals AS T1 JOIN Treatments AS T2 ON T1.professional_id  =  T2.professional_id

column5: Which owner owns the most dogs? List the owner id, first name and last name.
column7: SELECT T1.owner_id ,  T2.first_name ,  T2.last_name FROM Dogs AS T1 JOIN Owners AS T2 ON T1.owner_id  =  T2.owner_id GROUP BY T1.owner_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

column5: Return the owner id, first name and last name of the owner who has the most dogs.
column7: SELECT T1.owner_id ,  T2.first_name ,  T2.last_name FROM Dogs AS T1 JOIN Owners AS T2 ON T1.owner_id  =  T2.owner_id GROUP BY T1.owner_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

column5: Which professionals have done at least two treatments? List the professional's id, role, and first name.
column7: SELECT T1.professional_id ,  T1.role_code ,  T1.first_name FROM Professionals AS T1 JOIN Treatments AS T2 ON T1.professional_id  =  T2.professional_id GROUP BY T1.professional_id HAVING count(*)  >=  2

column5: What are the id, role, and first name of the professionals who have performed two or more treatments?
column7: SELECT T1.professional_id ,  T1.role_code ,  T1.first_name FROM Professionals AS T1 JOIN Treatments AS T2 ON T1.professional_id  =  T2.professional_id GROUP BY T1.professional_id HAVING count(*)  >=  2

column5: What is the name of the breed with the most dogs?
column7: SELECT T1.breed_name FROM Breeds AS T1 JOIN Dogs AS T2 ON T1.breed_code  =  T2.breed_code GROUP BY T1.breed_name ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

column5: Which breed do the most dogs have? Give me the breed name.
column7: SELECT T1.breed_name FROM Breeds AS T1 JOIN Dogs AS T2 ON T1.breed_code  =  T2.breed_code GROUP BY T1.breed_name ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

column5: What is the description of the treatment type that costs the least money in total?
column7: SELECT T1.treatment_type_description FROM Treatment_types AS T1 JOIN Treatments AS T2 ON T1.treatment_type_code  =  T2.treatment_type_code GROUP BY T1.treatment_type_code ORDER BY sum(cost_of_treatment) ASC LIMIT 1

column5: Give me the description of the treatment type whose total cost is the lowest.
column7: SELECT T1.treatment_type_description FROM Treatment_types AS T1 JOIN Treatments AS T2 ON T1.treatment_type_code  =  T2.treatment_type_code GROUP BY T1.treatment_type_code ORDER BY sum(cost_of_treatment) ASC LIMIT 1

column5: Which professionals have done at least two types of treatments? List the professional id and cell phone.
column7: SELECT T1.professional_id ,  T1.cell_number FROM Professionals AS T1 JOIN Treatments AS T2 ON T1.professional_id  =  T2.professional_id GROUP BY T1.professional_id HAVING count(*)  >=  2

column5: Find the id and cell phone of the professionals who operate two or more types of treatments.
column7: SELECT T1.professional_id ,  T1.cell_number FROM Professionals AS T1 JOIN Treatments AS T2 ON T1.professional_id  =  T2.professional_id GROUP BY T1.professional_id HAVING count(*)  >=  2

column5: What are the first name and last name of the professionals who have done treatment with cost below average?
column7: SELECT DISTINCT T1.first_name ,  T1.last_name FROM Professionals AS T1 JOIN Treatments AS T2 WHERE cost_of_treatment  <  ( SELECT avg(cost_of_treatment) FROM Treatments )

column5: Which professionals have operated a treatment that costs less than the average? Give me theor first names and last names.
column7: SELECT DISTINCT T1.first_name ,  T1.last_name FROM Professionals AS T1 JOIN Treatments AS T2 WHERE cost_of_treatment  <  ( SELECT avg(cost_of_treatment) FROM Treatments )

column5: List the date of each treatment, together with the first name of the professional who operated it.
column7: SELECT T1.date_of_treatment ,  T2.first_name FROM Treatments AS T1 JOIN Professionals AS T2 ON T1.professional_id  =  T2.professional_id

column5: What are the date and the operating professional's first name of each treatment?
column7: SELECT T1.date_of_treatment ,  T2.first_name FROM Treatments AS T1 JOIN Professionals AS T2 ON T1.professional_id  =  T2.professional_id

column5: List the cost of each treatment and the corresponding treatment type description.
column7: SELECT T1.cost_of_treatment ,  T2.treatment_type_description FROM Treatments AS T1 JOIN treatment_types AS T2 ON T1.treatment_type_code  =  T2.treatment_type_code

column5: What are the cost and treatment type description of each treatment?
column7: SELECT T1.cost_of_treatment ,  T2.treatment_type_description FROM Treatments AS T1 JOIN treatment_types AS T2 ON T1.treatment_type_code  =  T2.treatment_type_code

column5: List each owner's first name, last name, and the size of his for her dog.

column5: What are each owner's first name, last name, and the size of their dog?

column5: List pairs of the owner's first name and the dogs's name.

column5: What are the names of ships docked at each docking location, along with their maximum capacities
column7:
SELECT 
    d.name AS docking_location,
    shipName AS ship_name,
    maxCapacity AS max_capacity
FROM 
    Ports d
JOIN 
     CruiseShips c ON c.port =  d.name;

SELECT 
    d.name AS docking_location,
    shipName AS ship_name,
    maxCapacity AS max_capacity
FROM 
    Cities d
JOIN 
     CruiseShips c ON c.city =  d.name;

SELECT 
     ct.name, d.name,
    shipName AS ship_name,
    maxCapacity AS max_capacity
FROM 
    Ports d
JOIN 
     CruiseShips c ON c.port =  d.name JOIN Cities ct ON c.city =  ct.name ;

column5: How many ships are docked at each docking location
column7:
SELECT 
    name AS docking_location,
    COUNT(*) AS total_ships
FROM 
    Ports
LEFT JOIN 
    CruiseShips ON CruiseShips.port =  Ports.name 
GROUP BY 
    name;

SELECT 
    name AS docking_location,
    COUNT(*) AS total_ships
FROM 
    Cities
LEFT JOIN 
    CruiseShips ON CruiseShips.city =  Cities.name 
GROUP BY 
    name;

SELECT 
    Cities.name, Ports.name,
    COUNT(*) AS total_ships
FROM 
    Ports
LEFT JOIN 
    CruiseShips ON CruiseShips.port =  Ports.name  JOIN Cities ON CruiseShips.city =  Cities.name  
GROUP BY 
    Cities.name, Ports.name;

column5: What's the office address and city for Alice's office location?
column7:
SELECT City.city_name, City.country, Office_Address.address, Office_Address.postal_code
FROM Office_Address
JOIN Internship ON Office_Address.id = Internship.office_address_id
JOIN Application ON Application.internship_id = Internship.id JOIN City ON City.id = Internship.city_id
WHERE Application.applicant_full_name LIKE "Alice %"

column5: What is the office address and city of TechCorp?
column7:
SELECT City.city_name, City.country, Office_Address.address, Office_Address.postal_code
FROM Office_Address
JOIN Internship ON Office_Address.id = Internship.office_address_id
JOIN Application ON Application.internship_id = Internship.id
JOIN Employee ON Employee.id = Application.employee_id
JOIN Department ON  Department.id = Employee.department_id
JOIN Company ON Department.company_id= Company.id JOIN City ON City.id = Internship.city_id
WHERE Company.company_name = "TechCorp"

column5: List each patients name and their 5 year survival rate.
column7:
SELECT ILLNESSES.fiveYearSurvivalRate, PATIENTS.fullname
FROM PATIENTS 
JOIN DIAGNOSES ON PATIENTS.id = DIAGNOSES.patientId 
JOIN ILLNESSES ON  DIAGNOSES.illnessId = ILLNESSES.illnessID

column5: Show the number of credits that students from each college and university completed and did not fail for the year 2021
column7:
SELECT college, university, SUM(C.credits) as Num_Credits
FROM Students S
LEFT JOIN CourseEnrollments E ON S.id = E.student_id
LEFT JOIN Courses C ON C.id = E.course_id
WHERE E.year = 2021
AND E.grade not like '%F%'

column5: How many students from each college and university are enrolled in Calculus I?

FROM Students S
LEFT JOIN CourseEnrollments E ON S.id = E.student_id
LEFT JOIN Courses C ON C.id = E.course_id AND title = 'Calculus I'

column5: What is the passing requirement for Michael Brown's exam?
What core concepts is Charlie studying?
column7:
select c.concept_name  
from EnrolledStudents e
inner join Students t on t.id = e.student_id
inner join School_Subjects s on s.subject_id = e.subject_id
left join Core_Concepts c on s.core_concept_id = c.concept_id
where t.name = 'Charlie'

column5: What core concepts are associated with the highest grade?
column7:
select c.concept_name
from EnrolledStudents e

column5: In what location and era was the episode "The Murder" set in?

WHERE Episode.title LIKE "%The Murder%"

    s.title = 'US Election Results'

column5: List the eligibility criteria and documentation requirements demanded for the largest loan.
column7:
SELECT Eligibility_Criteria.criteria, Eligibility_Criteria.score, Documentation_Requirements.doc_type, Documentation_Requirements.requirement  FROM Eligibility_Criteria JOIN Loans ON Loans.eligibility_criteria_id = Eligibility_Criteria.id JOIN Documentation_Requirements ON Loans.Documentation_Requirement_id = Documentation_Requirements.id  WHERE

column5: Show the top 3 cities and countries by the total number of bank accounts.
column7:
SELECT c.name, l.name, COUNT(a.account_number) AS total_accounts
FROM City l
JOIN Banks b ON l.id = b.city_id
JOIN Accounts a ON b.id = a.owner_id JOIN Country c ON c.id = b.country_id
GROUP BY l.name
ORDER BY total_accounts DESC
LIMIT 3

column5: What is the percentage distribution of annual revenue per occupational category?
column7:
SELECT 
    Primary_Industry,
    SUM(AnnualRevenue) AS RevenuePerOccupationalDistribution,
    (SUM(AnnualRevenue) * 100.0) / SUM(SUM(AnnualRevenue)) OVER () AS PercentageOfTotalAnnualRevenue
FROM 
    Industries
GROUP BY 
    Primary_Industry;

SELECT 
    Most_Common_Job,
    SUM(AnnualRevenue) AS RevenuePerOccupationalDistribution,
    (SUM(AnnualRevenue) * 100.0) / SUM(SUM(AnnualRevenue)) OVER () AS PercentageOfTotalAnnualRevenue
FROM 
    Industries
GROUP BY 
    Most_Common_Job;

SELECT 
    Primary_Industry, Most_Common_Job,
    SUM(AnnualRevenue) AS RevenuePerOccupationalDistribution,
    (SUM(AnnualRevenue) * 100.0) / SUM(SUM(AnnualRevenue)) OVER () AS PercentageOfTotalAnnualRevenue
FROM 
    Industries
GROUP BY 
    Primary_Industry, Most_Common_Job;

column5: What is the average annual revenue per employee for each unique combination of industry ID and occupational distribution?
column7:
SELECT 
    IndustryID, 
    Primary_Industry,
    SUM(AnnualRevenue) / SUM(NumberOfEmployees) AS AnnualRevenuePerEmployee
FROM 
    Industries
GROUP BY 
    IndustryID, Primary_Industry;

SELECT 
    IndustryID, 
    Most_Common_Job,
    SUM(AnnualRevenue) / SUM(NumberOfEmployees) AS AnnualRevenuePerEmployee
FROM 
    Industries
GROUP BY 
    IndustryID, Most_Common_Job;

SELECT 
    IndustryID, 
    Primary_Industry, Most_Common_Job,
    SUM(AnnualRevenue) / SUM(NumberOfEmployees) AS AnnualRevenuePerEmployee
FROM 
    Industries
GROUP BY 
    IndustryID, Primary_Industry, Most_Common_Job;

column5: What is the lifecycle of the stadium construction project?
column7:
SELECT min_years, max_years
FROM Service_Life_Expectancy AS L 
LEFT JOIN Infrastructure AS I ON I.service_life_expectancy_id = L.service_life_expectancy_id 
LEFT JOIN Projects AS P ON P.infrastructure_id = I.infrastructure_id
WHERE P.name = 'Stadium Construction'

SELECT frequency
FROM Renewal_Schedule AS L 
LEFT JOIN Infrastructure AS I ON I.Renewal_Schedule_id = L.Renewal_Schedule_id 
LEFT JOIN Projects AS P ON P.infrastructure_id = I.infrastructure_id
WHERE P.name = 'Stadium Construction'

SELECT min_years, max_years, frequency
FROM Service_Life_Expectancy AS L 
LEFT JOIN Infrastructure AS I ON I.service_life_expectancy_id = L.service_life_expectancy_id 
LEFT JOIN Projects AS P ON P.infrastructure_id = I.infrastructure_id LEFT JOIN Renewal_Schedule AS RS ON I.Renewal_Schedule_id = RS.Renewal_Schedule_id
WHERE P.name = 'Stadium Construction'

column5: State the service lifecycle of each project due to end in 2023
column7:
SELECT name, min_years, max_years
FROM Projects AS P 
LEFT JOIN Infrastructure AS I ON P.infrastructure_id = I.infrastructure_id
LEFT JOIN Service_Life_Expectancy AS L ON I.service_life_expectancy_id = L.service_life_expectancy_id 
WHERE P.end_date BETWEEN '2023-01-01' AND '2023-12-31'

column5: What is the service lifecycle and renewal schedule of the stadium construction project?

SELECT min_years, max_years, frequency
FROM Service_Life_Expectancy AS L 
LEFT JOIN Infrastructure AS I ON I.service_life_expectancy_id = L.service_life_expectancy_id 
LEFT JOIN Projects AS P ON P.infrastructure_id = I.infrastructure_id LEFT JOIN Renewal_Schedule AS RS ON I.Renewal_Schedule_id = RS.Renewal_Schedule_id
WHERE P.name = 'Stadium Construction'

column5: For each customer and their resident cities, list all their transactions where the amount is less than 1000. Order this list by first date, and value i.e. for transactions that take place on the same date, list the smallest amounts first.
column7:
SELECT
Accounts.AccountNumber,
Customers.FullName,
Transactions.Amount,
Transactions.TransactionDate,
Addresses.City
FROM Accounts
JOIN Customers ON Customers.CustomerID = Accounts.CustomerID
JOIN Transactions ON Transactions.AccountNumber = Accounts.AccountNumber
JOIN Addresses ON Addresses.CustomerID = Accounts.CustomerID
WHERE Transactions.Amount < '1000'
ORDER BY Transactions.TransactionDate ASC, Transactions.Amount ASC

column5: What city did the cheapest flight depart from and what are the coordinates of that place?
column7:
SELECT A.City, Coordinates
FROM Airports A
JOIN Flights F
    ON A.IATA_Code = F.IATA_Departure
ORDER BY F.Price ASC
LIMIT 1;

column5: What are the headquarter coordinates of the airline with the most flights and the corresponding city?
column7:
SELECT A.City, Coordinates
FROM Airports A
JOIN Flights F
    ON A.IATA_Code = F.IATA_Departure
JOIN Airlines AL
    ON F.ForeignKey_Airline = AL.Airlines_Id
WHERE
    AL.Airlines_Id = (
        SELECT ForeignKey_Airline
        FROM Flights
        GROUP BY ForeignKey_Airline
        ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC
        LIMIT 1
    );

column5: What is the weight restriction and linear dimensions for the plane departing the runway with length 5000 at 11:00 on the 4th January?

column5: Show the list of flights, their plane manufacturers, source and destination airports with their departure date and times and order the list by date and time.
column7:
SELECT
Flights.flight_number,
Planes.manufacturer_name,
Source.name, 
Dest.name,
Flights.departure_date,
Flights.scheduled_departure_time
FROM Flights
JOIN Planes ON Planes.id = Flights.plane_id
JOIN Routes ON Routes.id = Flights.route_id
JOIN Airports AS Source ON Source.id = Routes.source_airport_id
JOIN Airports AS Dest ON Dest.id = Routes.destination_airport_id
ORDER BY Flights.departure_date ASC, Flights.scheduled_departure_time ASC

JOIN AssignsPilotToFlight APTF ON APTF.flight_id = Flights.id
JOIN Pilots ON Pilots.id = APTF.pilot_id
JOIN Airlines ON Airlines.id = Routes.airline_id

column5: For each customer and their resident cities and countries, list all their transactions where the amount is less than 1000. Order this list by first date, and value i.e. for transactions that take place on the same date, list the smallest amounts first.

Accounts.AccountNumber,
Customers.FullName,
Transactions.Amount,

JOIN Addresses ON Addresses.CustomerID = Accounts.CustomerID

ORDER BY Transactions.TransactionDate ASC, Transactions.Amount ASC

column5: What are the full names of customers with the highest total balance in their accounts and who is the the CEO of the branches they use?
column7:
SELECT 
    c.fullName,
    SUM(a.balance) AS Total_Balance,
    b.Ceo
FROM Customers c
JOIN Accounts a
    ON c.customerId = a.customerId
JOIN Banks b
    ON c.bankID = b.id
GROUP BY c.customerId
ORDER BY Total_Balance DESC

column5: List the management team members of the bank that receives the greatest monthly payment.
column7:

    b.Management_Team AS Bank_Leader
FROM Banks b
JOIN Customers c
    ON b.id = c.bankID
JOIN Loans l
    ON c.customerId = l.customerId
GROUP BY 
    b.Management_Team
ORDER BY 
    monthlyPayment DESC
LIMIT 1;

column5: Show the campus building and online platform ranked by the most highly subscribed lecture along with the lecture titles.
column7:
SELECT v.name, p.platformName, 
             l.title as 'Lecture Title'
FROM Campus_Building v 
JOIN Lecture L on campusId = v.id JOIN Online_Platform P on L.onlineId = P.id
JOIN (SELECT
         COUNT(StudentId) as Attendance,
         lectureId
         FROM Enrollment
         GROUP BY lectureID) e ON e.lectureID = L.id

column5: What software is used for Introductory Organic Chemistry?
column7:
SELECT 
    r.name AS Resource_Title
FROM 
    Courses c
    INNER JOIN Software r ON c.Software_id = r.id
WHERE 
    c.course_name = 'Introductory Organic Chemistry';

column5: Which field of study is the focus of project scoring more than 90 points?
column7:
SELECT 
    f.name 
FROM 
    Enrollment e
    INNER JOIN Project p ON e.projectId = p.id
    INNER JOIN Field_Of_Study f 
ON p.FieldOfStudyId = f.id 
AND e.grade > 90;

column5: Which topic and field of study is the focus of project scoring more than 90 points?
column7:
SELECT 
    f.name, fs.name
FROM 
    Enrollment e
    INNER JOIN Project p ON e.projectId = p.id
    INNER JOIN Topic f 
ON p.topicId = f.id 
 INNER JOIN Field_Of_Study fs 
ON p.FieldOfStudyId = fs.id 
AND e.grade > 90;
